1
00:00:01,913 --> 00:00:03,633
Love line prediction game, Heart Signal.

2
00:00:03,633 --> 00:00:09,003
Five people with sharp romance
radars have gathered.

3
00:00:09,003 --> 00:00:10,793
This couple got people talking last week.

4
00:00:10,793 --> 00:00:13,493
Wu Yeol and Yu Gyeong's pork belly date.

5
00:00:13,493 --> 00:00:15,323
It was the first time we felt at peace.

6
00:00:15,323 --> 00:00:20,113
He hasn't said anything reassuring
before, but...

7
00:00:20,113 --> 00:00:23,853
The only person who expressed
their feeling for him

8
00:00:23,853 --> 00:00:26,213
directly was Yu Gyeong.

9
00:00:26,213 --> 00:00:27,893
[The moment they confirmed
their feelings for each other]

10
00:00:27,893 --> 00:00:30,203
It probably let them know clearly.

11
00:00:30,203 --> 00:00:33,803
- And his apology.
- That was important.

12
00:00:33,803 --> 00:00:35,543
Sorry.

13
00:00:35,543 --> 00:00:39,943
As someone who had said that
more than anyone in life,

14
00:00:39,943 --> 00:00:41,553
I know he said that because

15
00:00:41,553 --> 00:00:46,313
he wants to maintain
the relationship with her.

16
00:00:46,313 --> 00:00:50,673
That's right. But married men
struggle to say sorry.

17
00:00:50,673 --> 00:00:52,173
We always hear the same response.

18
00:00:52,173 --> 00:00:54,303
"What are you sorry about?'

19
00:00:54,303 --> 00:00:55,963
We always say it in advance.

20
00:00:55,963 --> 00:00:57,533
[Sorry in advance?]

21
00:00:57,533 --> 00:01:00,433
The two couples
ran into each other by chance.

22
00:01:00,433 --> 00:01:02,243
I only remember Gyu Ri's face.

23
00:01:02,243 --> 00:01:04,423
It must've affected her a lot.

24
00:01:04,423 --> 00:01:08,093
And she cried while coming down
on the escalator.

25
00:01:08,093 --> 00:01:11,223
I don't think it was because of the movie.

26
00:01:11,223 --> 00:01:14,603
Being there was like an escape for her,

27
00:01:14,603 --> 00:01:18,403
but she ended up in the worst
situation imaginable.

28
00:01:18,403 --> 00:01:22,493
And I think she felt guilty that
she was feeling that way

29
00:01:22,493 --> 00:01:25,423
- in front of Seo Won.
- I think so, too.

30
00:01:25,423 --> 00:01:31,743
But I could tell that Seo Won
really likes Gyu Ri.

31
00:01:31,743 --> 00:01:35,003
While she was feeling down and guilty,

32
00:01:35,003 --> 00:01:38,053
he was like, "That's your charm."

33
00:01:38,053 --> 00:01:40,303
I guess Gyu Ri must not see that in Seo Won.

34
00:01:40,303 --> 00:01:44,363
He's always a step behind her.

35
00:01:44,363 --> 00:01:47,723
So Yun approached Wu Yeol with the scarf.

36
00:01:47,723 --> 00:01:49,223
- So sad.
- I feel so bad for her.

37
00:01:49,223 --> 00:01:54,343
So Yun seemed so upset that day,

38
00:01:54,343 --> 00:01:59,203
but would her feelings for Wu Yeol stay?

39
00:01:59,203 --> 00:02:01,153
I think the ring affected her a lot.

40
00:02:01,153 --> 00:02:04,293
- It was a big deal.
- Yes, getting rings is significant.

41
00:02:04,293 --> 00:02:10,643
Let's check out what happens
in Signal House after the stormy day.

42
00:02:11,483 --> 00:02:13,503
So Yun.

43
00:02:13,503 --> 00:02:14,993
Did you wait long?

44
00:02:14,993 --> 00:02:17,553
- It's cold, isn't it?
- Yes, a little bit.

45
00:02:17,553 --> 00:02:21,403
- Tokushima was so warm.
- I know, it was.

46
00:02:21,403 --> 00:02:24,903
I can no longer gauge the weather.

47
00:02:26,513 --> 00:02:27,853
This is it.

48
00:02:27,853 --> 00:02:30,053
Wow, it's huge.

49
00:02:30,053 --> 00:02:34,893
I want to get a purse for work.

50
00:02:35,723 --> 00:02:38,843
- I love the interior design here.
- It's nice.

51
00:02:38,843 --> 00:02:41,833
Wow, the second floor is huge.

52
00:02:42,783 --> 00:02:45,373
The red one is pretty, too.

53
00:02:45,373 --> 00:02:47,063
- So pretty.
- It suits you well.

54
00:02:47,063 --> 00:02:49,023
Does it?

55
00:02:49,023 --> 00:02:50,703
- What do you think?
- It's pretty.

56
00:02:50,703 --> 00:02:53,863
- They know how to use colors.
- I know.

57
00:02:53,863 --> 00:02:56,163
Recommend one for my look right now.

58
00:02:56,163 --> 00:02:58,713
Something that suits you? Come here.

59
00:02:59,493 --> 00:03:03,173
- This brown one suits you.
- Is it brown for me today?

60
00:03:03,173 --> 00:03:05,583
- Wow, it's pretty.
- It's perfect.

61
00:03:05,583 --> 00:03:09,043
- It's pretty.
- I think I need to buy this.

62
00:03:09,043 --> 00:03:12,103
This looks like my Mongul.

63
00:03:12,103 --> 00:03:14,993
- We got matching ones.
- I know.

64
00:03:14,993 --> 00:03:19,083
I'm happy that the shopping was a success.

65
00:03:19,083 --> 00:03:22,003
[Bought matching purses]

66
00:03:22,603 --> 00:03:23,623
[A makchang* restaurant in Yongsan-gu]
(Tripe)

67
00:03:23,623 --> 00:03:25,363
Looks so tasty.

68
00:03:26,853 --> 00:03:30,903
Isn't the scallion makchang famous?

69
00:03:30,903 --> 00:03:32,303
Here's the fire.

70
00:03:32,303 --> 00:03:34,893
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

71
00:03:34,893 --> 00:03:37,843
It's Sunday today.

72
00:03:37,843 --> 00:03:39,333
- Let's go out.
- I know.

73
00:03:39,333 --> 00:03:41,273
- Are you driving?
- Yes, I'll drive.

74
00:03:41,273 --> 00:03:42,963
- We have a car right now.
- Okay.

75
00:03:42,963 --> 00:03:45,503
- How does gopchang sound?
- I'd love it.

76
00:03:45,503 --> 00:03:47,993
- Really? Let's get gopchang, then.
- They're so pretty.

77
00:03:47,993 --> 00:03:50,773
Let's go get gopchang.

78
00:03:52,373 --> 00:03:54,163
[Warming up]

79
00:03:54,163 --> 00:03:55,903
It's pretty cold.

80
00:03:55,903 --> 00:03:58,443
My hands feel cold.

81
00:04:00,293 --> 00:04:05,033
- That looks so good. What's inside?
- Isn't it makchang?

82
00:04:05,033 --> 00:04:06,463
Thanks for the meal.

83
00:04:06,463 --> 00:04:07,953
[Yum]

84
00:04:07,953 --> 00:04:10,373
[Serious eyebrows]

85
00:04:10,373 --> 00:04:12,013
[Mmm]

86
00:04:12,013 --> 00:04:14,343
This is seriously delicious.

87
00:04:14,343 --> 00:04:17,073
[Time to get things off their chest]

88
00:04:17,073 --> 00:04:18,953
Start talking about your dating lives.

89
00:04:18,953 --> 00:04:22,513
They will. Min Ju and So Yun are there.

90
00:04:24,863 --> 00:04:27,463
It's gotten easier to eat, hasn't it?
Do you agree?

91
00:04:27,463 --> 00:04:28,693
- Eating food?
- Yes.

92
00:04:28,693 --> 00:04:31,533
- Me, too. I had a hard time eating.
- Me, too.

93
00:04:31,533 --> 00:04:33,953
You joined later than we did.

94
00:04:33,953 --> 00:04:36,133
Could you get the gist of things?

95
00:04:36,133 --> 00:04:37,533
You mean, how people feel?

96
00:04:37,533 --> 00:04:39,713
- Other people?
- Yes.

97
00:04:39,713 --> 00:04:42,783
Yes. I think I see most of it.

98
00:04:42,783 --> 00:04:44,693
I couldn't tell at first.

99
00:04:44,693 --> 00:04:47,283
But I saw a lot in Japan.

100
00:04:47,283 --> 00:04:49,513
To me, it was on the boat.

101
00:04:49,513 --> 00:04:51,663
- On the boat.
- I see.

102
00:04:51,663 --> 00:04:54,333
But I was with Jun Hyeon.

103
00:04:54,333 --> 00:04:56,603
So what? Why shouldn't you be?

104
00:04:56,603 --> 00:04:59,843
Aren't you ruling him out too much?

105
00:04:59,843 --> 00:05:03,573
I was just with him. I was with Jun Hyeon.

106
00:05:03,573 --> 00:05:06,453
- Summarize it for us.
- Tell us. Who likes whom?

107
00:05:06,453 --> 00:05:08,773
- Summarize it for us.
- Just tell us.

108
00:05:08,773 --> 00:05:10,463
Let's see how accurate she is.

109
00:05:10,463 --> 00:05:12,613
- Including you, too?
- Yes.

110
00:05:12,613 --> 00:05:14,323
- Are you serious?
- Yes.

111
00:05:14,323 --> 00:05:16,853
- Are you curious?
- Yes, I am.

112
00:05:17,853 --> 00:05:19,893
Should we drink first, then?

113
00:05:19,893 --> 00:05:21,403
You can include us.

114
00:05:21,403 --> 00:05:23,793
- This will be fun.
- Drink first.

115
00:05:23,793 --> 00:05:25,783
This is fun.

116
00:05:25,783 --> 00:05:28,863
- I think So Yun would be fun to talk to.
- I know.

117
00:05:28,863 --> 00:05:30,573
[Nervous]

118
00:05:31,343 --> 00:05:33,303
First of all, I like Wu Yeol.

119
00:05:33,303 --> 00:05:35,093
[Daebak]

120
00:05:35,093 --> 00:05:36,363
Wow.

121
00:05:36,363 --> 00:05:38,873
- She's starting with herself.
- Wow, daebak.

122
00:05:38,873 --> 00:05:41,273
I feel like I just got smacked in the face.

123
00:05:41,273 --> 00:05:46,043
I didn't think her first words
would be Wu Yeol.

124
00:05:46,043 --> 00:05:48,003
First of all, I like Wu Yeol.

125
00:05:48,003 --> 00:05:49,073
[Gasp]

126
00:05:49,803 --> 00:05:51,933
Wow, hold on. How...

127
00:05:51,933 --> 00:05:55,423
I was asked on the first day.

128
00:05:55,423 --> 00:06:00,073
When I see him,
I decide in the first 3 seconds.

129
00:06:00,073 --> 00:06:01,493
Did you decide?

130
00:06:01,493 --> 00:06:03,253
Yes, I did.

131
00:06:03,253 --> 00:06:06,413
It's been Wu Yeol since then.

132
00:06:06,413 --> 00:06:08,673
He's the closest to being my type.

133
00:06:08,673 --> 00:06:10,533
But the trip to Japan affected me a lot.

134
00:06:10,533 --> 00:06:13,093
- You were together in Japan.
- Right.

135
00:06:13,093 --> 00:06:15,323
I just found him cute.

136
00:06:15,323 --> 00:06:17,713
I found his pureness cute.

137
00:06:17,713 --> 00:06:21,003
[First time hearing about So Yun's feelings]

138
00:06:22,413 --> 00:06:26,323
That made things harder for me, too.

139
00:06:26,323 --> 00:06:28,733
Although some things improved.

140
00:06:28,733 --> 00:06:31,613
- Let's drink.
- Let's drink. Let's.

141
00:06:31,613 --> 00:06:36,583
It's important to tell them
because they're involved, too.

142
00:06:36,583 --> 00:06:37,493
[Startled]

143
00:06:37,493 --> 00:06:38,623
- You scared me.
- What?

144
00:06:38,623 --> 00:06:41,863
- Is someone coming in?
- Wait. My gosh!

145
00:06:41,863 --> 00:06:45,353
- Wow, what timing.
- Are you joining us?

146
00:06:45,353 --> 00:06:47,643
Could you give us five minutes?

147
00:06:47,643 --> 00:06:50,683
- We're having a serious conversation.
- Keep going. Keep going.

148
00:06:50,683 --> 00:06:53,373
- What? Seriously.
- Why are you so late?

149
00:06:53,373 --> 00:06:55,693
- Are you coming from work?
- I am.

150
00:06:55,693 --> 00:06:58,033
[He joined them after a busy day]

151
00:06:59,163 --> 00:07:03,853
We were just saying how you'd be home alone,

152
00:07:03,853 --> 00:07:05,583
- and you came.
- Right.

153
00:07:05,583 --> 00:07:07,243
I was worried.

154
00:07:07,243 --> 00:07:09,813
Thank you. What were you talking about?

155
00:07:10,563 --> 00:07:15,063
- Wu Yeol.
- I'm not sure what Wu Yeol is thinking.

156
00:07:15,063 --> 00:07:17,083
[Nodding]

157
00:07:17,833 --> 00:07:23,113
I'm curious how he feels.
I'll probably ask him later.

158
00:07:23,113 --> 00:07:25,323
But I'm not going to be like,

159
00:07:25,323 --> 00:07:27,993
- "What's with you?" to his face.
- Of course not.

160
00:07:27,993 --> 00:07:30,563
Of course not. We'll just talk naturally.

161
00:07:30,563 --> 00:07:33,623
I probably could figure out how he feels.

162
00:07:34,553 --> 00:07:37,913
Except for myself,

163
00:07:37,913 --> 00:07:40,683
Seo Won and Gyu Ri seem so obvious.

164
00:07:40,683 --> 00:07:43,233
Really? Do they like each other?

165
00:07:43,233 --> 00:07:46,253
- I can't gauge Gyu Ri.
- Really?

166
00:07:47,253 --> 00:07:49,473
I think you...

167
00:07:49,473 --> 00:07:51,003
[Flustered]

168
00:07:51,003 --> 00:07:52,923
Should we drink?

169
00:07:52,923 --> 00:07:55,193
Are you starting to sweat?

170
00:07:55,193 --> 00:07:56,863
No, I'm not.

171
00:07:57,783 --> 00:07:59,603
[Ears perking]

172
00:07:59,603 --> 00:08:01,293
I think you like Yu Gyeong and MIn Ju.

173
00:08:01,293 --> 00:08:03,953
- Right, right.
- Yes, she knows.

174
00:08:03,953 --> 00:08:05,143
[Drinking]

175
00:08:05,143 --> 00:08:08,763
We can't talk about this
outside of Self Talk.

176
00:08:08,763 --> 00:08:11,383
Who leaked the information?

177
00:08:12,863 --> 00:08:16,063
- You're right. You're right.
- And Min Ju...

178
00:08:17,723 --> 00:08:18,633
[Laughing]

179
00:08:18,633 --> 00:08:21,453
- likes Seong Min.
- Wow, she's saying all that.

180
00:08:21,453 --> 00:08:23,013
I know.

181
00:08:23,863 --> 00:08:25,263
And Oppa?

182
00:08:25,263 --> 00:08:27,373
- I find him most mysterious.
- I do, too.

183
00:08:27,373 --> 00:08:30,383
Maybe you like Gyu Ri?

184
00:08:30,383 --> 00:08:31,713
[Mysterious laughter]

185
00:08:31,713 --> 00:08:35,813
- She doesn't know that he likes Yu Gyeong.
- I'm not so sure.

186
00:08:35,813 --> 00:08:38,753
- I'm just starting to...
- Starting to learn now?

187
00:08:39,943 --> 00:08:42,413
[Pressuring him silently]

188
00:08:42,413 --> 00:08:44,573
[Pressured]

189
00:08:45,233 --> 00:08:48,083
- Do you go to work tomorrow?
- Yes, of course.

190
00:08:48,083 --> 00:08:50,333
Everyone is waiting for your answer.

191
00:08:50,333 --> 00:08:52,973
I can't gauge you, either. I really can't.

192
00:08:53,883 --> 00:08:56,633
- Does Min Ju know?
- I think I like one person.

193
00:08:56,633 --> 00:08:58,963
Okay. That's good enough.

194
00:08:59,913 --> 00:09:01,733
As of now.

195
00:09:03,293 --> 00:09:05,283
Didn't I tell you earlier?

196
00:09:07,093 --> 00:09:09,863
- You know, I...
- What?

197
00:09:11,533 --> 00:09:13,763
I'm tired.

198
00:09:13,763 --> 00:09:16,413
- I like Min Ju and Yu Gyeong.
- Min Ju and Yu Gyeong.

199
00:09:16,413 --> 00:09:17,723
He said Min Ju first.

200
00:09:17,723 --> 00:09:20,013
That's exactly what I said earlier.

201
00:09:20,013 --> 00:09:22,923
It must be awkward because
you're together right now.

202
00:09:22,923 --> 00:09:24,363
- I know.
- Does it matter?

203
00:09:24,363 --> 00:09:26,103
That's why I didn't want to say it.

204
00:09:26,103 --> 00:09:29,553
But we already talked about this in Japan.

205
00:09:29,553 --> 00:09:32,603
But that cafe was a bit weird.

206
00:09:32,603 --> 00:09:33,723
Why are you laughing?

207
00:09:33,723 --> 00:09:36,003
The cafe was weird?

208
00:09:36,003 --> 00:09:39,003
- Something was going on there.
- It was cursed.

209
00:09:39,003 --> 00:09:41,123
How was it weird, exactly?

210
00:09:41,123 --> 00:09:43,193
- How did we get here?
- What are we doing?

211
00:09:43,193 --> 00:09:45,823
- How did we get here?
- It was the clock.

212
00:09:46,953 --> 00:09:50,563
That clock rang our hearts. Seriously.

213
00:09:50,563 --> 00:09:53,033
I don't know the answer yet.

214
00:09:53,033 --> 00:09:57,013
I don't think it's just one person.

215
00:09:57,013 --> 00:10:00,793
My feelings have changed
since we got back from Japan.

216
00:10:00,793 --> 00:10:02,893
He was swayed. He was swayed.

217
00:10:02,893 --> 00:10:05,003
My feelings changed a lot.

218
00:10:05,003 --> 00:10:07,593
While riding a bike?

219
00:10:07,593 --> 00:10:10,183
She's smiling.

220
00:10:10,183 --> 00:10:12,183
That was an excellent date.

221
00:10:12,183 --> 00:10:13,253
[Smiling]

222
00:10:13,253 --> 00:10:16,153
We got a lot off our chests.

223
00:10:16,153 --> 00:10:17,973
- In my opinion.
- After the talk?

224
00:10:17,973 --> 00:10:19,683
This is so...

225
00:10:20,943 --> 00:10:22,263
[Looking]

226
00:10:23,533 --> 00:10:26,563
I have feelings for Oppa,

227
00:10:26,563 --> 00:10:29,463
but there's another person I'm curious about.

228
00:10:30,493 --> 00:10:31,913
That's all.

229
00:10:31,913 --> 00:10:34,053
Do I have to tell you who that is?

230
00:10:34,053 --> 00:10:37,243
- No, it's okay.
- Of course not.

231
00:10:37,243 --> 00:10:39,953
[First time speaking her mind]

232
00:10:39,953 --> 00:10:41,543
- I don't know.
- I don't, either.

233
00:10:41,543 --> 00:10:44,103
This is your first time hearing this, too.

234
00:10:44,103 --> 00:10:45,623
Right.

235
00:10:46,623 --> 00:10:52,623
I think I should be more honest
about my feelings.

236
00:10:54,723 --> 00:10:58,063
Doesn't he look surprised that
there's someone else?

237
00:10:58,063 --> 00:11:00,943
Do you have a strategy?
Your feelings are clear.

238
00:11:00,943 --> 00:11:03,513
- Your heart leans toward Wu Yeol.
- Strategy?

239
00:11:03,513 --> 00:11:06,833
- How will you make his...
- I think you must have one.

240
00:11:06,833 --> 00:11:08,953
I think she has a strategy.

241
00:11:08,953 --> 00:11:10,743
- I think you're a strategic type.
- Strategy?

242
00:11:10,743 --> 00:11:14,153
I've never strategically seduced anyone.

243
00:11:14,153 --> 00:11:15,323
Isn't that a strategy?

244
00:11:15,323 --> 00:11:17,843
No, no. Here's what I believe.

245
00:11:17,843 --> 00:11:20,043
If it's meant to be,
it doesn't matter what I do.

246
00:11:20,043 --> 00:11:22,513
If it's not, I can't do anything about it

247
00:11:22,513 --> 00:11:27,403
Instead, I regret it if I don't do my best.

248
00:11:27,403 --> 00:11:29,273
- You just want to do your best.
- Yes, and...

249
00:11:29,273 --> 00:11:31,003
Nice and simple.

250
00:11:31,003 --> 00:11:33,413
To be honest,
I feel a little scared right now.

251
00:11:33,413 --> 00:11:36,833
I'm scared to ask him, too. And...

252
00:11:39,223 --> 00:11:40,993
since I'm a human, too,

253
00:11:40,993 --> 00:11:46,283
if the person I like doesn't seem to like me,

254
00:11:46,283 --> 00:11:48,123
I feel small.

255
00:11:48,123 --> 00:11:49,363
It's been affecting her.

256
00:11:49,363 --> 00:11:57,053
I prefer to hear the other person's
honest feelings and move on.

257
00:11:57,053 --> 00:12:00,433
But I'm not planning to give up at all.

258
00:12:00,433 --> 00:12:04,553
- I think things still can change.
- Right.

259
00:12:04,553 --> 00:12:07,053
Rather than strategizing,

260
00:12:07,053 --> 00:12:09,923
I want to just observe for now.

261
00:12:09,923 --> 00:12:11,673
That's nice.

262
00:12:11,673 --> 00:12:16,633
Jun Hyeon, don't just make filler noises.

263
00:12:16,633 --> 00:12:19,473
I'm feeling and learning a lot today.
I didn't expect it.

264
00:12:19,473 --> 00:12:21,773
Seong Min learns too much all the time.

265
00:12:21,773 --> 00:12:24,143
- He always says he's learning.
- Jun Hyeon is funny.

266
00:12:24,143 --> 00:12:26,663
- He's always learning.
-Stop studying.

267
00:12:26,663 --> 00:12:29,773
- Start teaching us now.
- You want me to teach you?

268
00:12:29,773 --> 00:12:32,283
- Are you here to learn?
- Please teach me.

269
00:12:32,283 --> 00:12:34,633
[The night is getting livelier]

270
00:12:34,633 --> 00:12:36,993
If the person you have feelings for

271
00:12:36,993 --> 00:12:40,043
is interested in someone else,
how would you feel?

272
00:12:40,043 --> 00:12:43,893
- It's heartbreaking.
- What would you think you should do?

273
00:12:46,903 --> 00:12:48,953
I think I'm similar to you.

274
00:12:48,953 --> 00:12:52,293
I'll just try to show them my good qualities.

275
00:12:52,293 --> 00:12:55,023
- I'll just keep doing that.
- That's his personality.

276
00:12:55,023 --> 00:12:58,403
But if it still doesn't work,

277
00:12:58,403 --> 00:13:00,963
I'll have to give up even if it's hard.

278
00:13:02,033 --> 00:13:07,493
Because I'll respect their
decision not to choose me.

279
00:13:07,493 --> 00:13:10,123
[Is Min Ju feeling the same way right now?]

280
00:13:11,953 --> 00:13:13,973
Just do as much as you can.

281
00:13:13,973 --> 00:13:18,113
The decision is up to the other person.

282
00:13:19,113 --> 00:13:20,313
[Turning]

283
00:13:20,313 --> 00:13:23,923
I'll be proactive somehow.

284
00:13:23,923 --> 00:13:26,063
This is so uncomfortable.

285
00:13:26,063 --> 00:13:29,923
But I'm still at the stage of observing.

286
00:13:29,923 --> 00:13:33,453
Once my feelings are totally confirmed,

287
00:13:34,403 --> 00:13:37,963
I'll probably forge ahead
without looking around.

288
00:13:37,963 --> 00:13:41,453
Right. But you haven't confirmed yet, huh?

289
00:13:41,453 --> 00:13:43,793
Confirmed?

290
00:13:43,793 --> 00:13:45,753
She might be saying that on purpose.

291
00:13:45,753 --> 00:13:47,163
[Eyes closing]

292
00:13:47,163 --> 00:13:51,023
But I'm the type who pursues aggressively.

293
00:13:51,023 --> 00:13:53,813
- I'm totally honest.
- You guys are similar, then.

294
00:13:53,813 --> 00:13:56,733
Right, they're a bit similar.

295
00:13:56,733 --> 00:13:58,203
[One glass]

296
00:13:58,203 --> 00:13:59,633
[Two glasses]

297
00:13:59,633 --> 00:14:01,263
[The glasses are getting emptied]

298
00:14:01,263 --> 00:14:05,483
I'm curious. You said
you like Wu Yeol, So Yun.

299
00:14:05,483 --> 00:14:09,133
Is everyone else just "others" to you?

300
00:14:10,443 --> 00:14:12,833
I was interested in Jun Hyeon at first, too.

301
00:14:12,833 --> 00:14:14,333
[Surprised]

302
00:14:14,333 --> 00:14:18,213
This is what she does. She's a bit...

303
00:14:18,213 --> 00:14:19,723
- What's wrong?
- I don't know...

304
00:14:19,723 --> 00:14:21,973
- This is so fun.
- What just happened?

305
00:14:21,973 --> 00:14:23,373
What's wrong?

306
00:14:24,343 --> 00:14:26,133
We've been so honest with each other.

307
00:14:26,133 --> 00:14:29,923
Let's hear who's on Jun Hyeon's
mind before we go.

308
00:14:29,923 --> 00:14:31,153
That's a great idea.

309
00:14:31,153 --> 00:14:33,533
- Jun Hyeon didn't show at all.
- Let's hear who that person is.

310
00:14:33,533 --> 00:14:35,153
No, not all of you spoke.

311
00:14:35,153 --> 00:14:37,723
- We all did.
- You didn't tell us.

312
00:14:37,723 --> 00:14:39,003
- What?
- You said you had two.

313
00:14:39,003 --> 00:14:41,393
It's you and you.

314
00:14:41,393 --> 00:14:43,423
Jun Hyeon?

315
00:14:43,423 --> 00:14:44,483
Daebak.

316
00:14:44,483 --> 00:14:46,933
Hold on, you close at 11?
Can we stay a bit longer?

317
00:14:46,933 --> 00:14:48,473
I like you and you.

318
00:14:48,473 --> 00:14:49,653
Hold on.

319
00:14:49,653 --> 00:14:51,423
I'm suddenly faced with my competition?

320
00:14:51,423 --> 00:14:53,093
Take a glass, Hyung.

321
00:14:53,973 --> 00:14:55,103
I'll give you a lot.

322
00:14:55,103 --> 00:14:57,063
[Two men are competing for Min Ju]

323
00:14:59,623 --> 00:15:01,913
The four of us have no secrets at all.

324
00:15:01,913 --> 00:15:03,463
Am I wrong?

325
00:15:03,463 --> 00:15:08,763
But there are still people we
haven't talked to properly yet.

326
00:15:08,763 --> 00:15:11,233
Did you go on a date with Yu Gyeong?

327
00:15:11,233 --> 00:15:12,593
He did.

328
00:15:12,593 --> 00:15:14,533
It was short.

329
00:15:14,533 --> 00:15:16,263
He's so sad about it.

330
00:15:17,693 --> 00:15:18,773
He really is.

331
00:15:18,773 --> 00:15:20,633
It was short. Dot, dot, dot.

332
00:15:20,633 --> 00:15:22,663
- He added dot, dot, dot.
- You sounded sad.

333
00:15:22,663 --> 00:15:24,583
Try to have a long date, then.

334
00:15:24,583 --> 00:15:27,273
- No, no, no.
- Take a trip to Jeju-do or something.

335
00:15:27,273 --> 00:15:28,993
What are you saying...

336
00:15:30,703 --> 00:15:31,713
[Exhaling]

337
00:15:33,363 --> 00:15:37,533
This gathering was very meaningful.

338
00:15:39,923 --> 00:15:42,413
- This was a strange gathering.
- What a fun conversation.

339
00:15:42,413 --> 00:15:43,673
Seong Min said something important.

340
00:15:43,673 --> 00:15:46,693
That his feelings have changed
a lot since the Japan trip.

341
00:15:46,693 --> 00:15:50,513
Don't you feel like Min Ju and Seong Min
have a better chance from this?

342
00:15:50,513 --> 00:15:52,513
The odds definitely increased.

343
00:15:52,513 --> 00:15:55,813
Everyone, the war is about to start now.

344
00:15:55,813 --> 00:15:57,693
What kind of war is it now?

345
00:15:57,693 --> 00:16:01,463
Everyone will gather at the house after this.

346
00:16:01,463 --> 00:16:03,983
I'm so curious how Wu Yeol would behave.

347
00:16:03,983 --> 00:16:06,493
I'm most curious about what he'd do.

348
00:16:06,493 --> 00:16:09,493
[The next day]

349
00:16:09,493 --> 00:16:11,493
[Busy]

350
00:16:13,733 --> 00:16:14,653
[Min Ju's first day at work]

351
00:16:14,653 --> 00:16:17,033
She's so pretty as usual.

352
00:16:17,033 --> 00:16:19,103
Where's your work, then?

353
00:16:19,103 --> 00:16:22,703
- It's near Hak-dong Station.
- Hak-dong Station.

354
00:16:22,703 --> 00:16:23,793
Hak-dong?

355
00:16:23,793 --> 00:16:26,033
- I'm kind of worried about it.
- Why?

356
00:16:26,033 --> 00:16:28,173
I have to transfer three times on the subway,

357
00:16:28,173 --> 00:16:30,093
but it's a 13-minute drive.

358
00:16:30,093 --> 00:16:32,143
Whose work is in that direction?

359
00:16:32,143 --> 00:16:34,083
Hak-dong? Me.

360
00:16:35,083 --> 00:16:36,433
What time, did you say?

361
00:16:36,433 --> 00:16:38,713
I can leave earlier.

362
00:16:38,713 --> 00:16:40,933
You'll arrive at 9:30.

363
00:16:40,933 --> 00:16:44,303
Really? I'd love to get there by 9:30.

364
00:16:44,303 --> 00:16:47,023
- What a relief.
- Is this how it starts?

365
00:16:47,023 --> 00:16:49,153
You can be commute buddies.

366
00:16:49,153 --> 00:16:50,873
She's so happy.

367
00:16:52,783 --> 00:16:54,153
[Tap, tap]

368
00:16:57,843 --> 00:17:00,983
[Getting ready, feeling excited]

369
00:17:00,983 --> 00:17:04,303
What a pivotal time.
They'll never forget this.

370
00:17:04,303 --> 00:17:07,643
[Seong Min is waiting for
Min Ju on the first floor]

371
00:17:08,243 --> 00:17:10,943
[Looking up the route]

372
00:17:12,663 --> 00:17:14,393
[Rushing]

373
00:17:16,573 --> 00:17:18,123
Hi.

374
00:17:18,123 --> 00:17:20,673
- Seong Min.
- Did you sleep well?

375
00:17:20,673 --> 00:17:24,133
- How do you feel? Are you nervous?
- No.

376
00:17:24,133 --> 00:17:26,563
- Really? Isn't this your first day?
- It is.

377
00:17:26,563 --> 00:17:29,863
But I think it will be fine.

378
00:17:29,863 --> 00:17:32,903
- She must nervous.
- Let's go.

379
00:17:32,903 --> 00:17:34,273
Let's go. Let's go.

380
00:17:34,273 --> 00:17:36,193
How nice.

381
00:17:38,423 --> 00:17:41,563
I'm suddenly starting to feel nervous.

382
00:17:42,873 --> 00:17:46,383
For some reason... For some reason...

383
00:17:47,333 --> 00:17:48,653
I feel weird.

384
00:17:48,653 --> 00:17:50,703
You feel weird?

385
00:17:50,703 --> 00:17:54,463
Going out with you in the morning
feels weird.

386
00:17:54,463 --> 00:17:56,163
She likes it, more like.

387
00:17:56,163 --> 00:17:59,843
It's cute how she keeps
expressing her feelings.

388
00:18:00,723 --> 00:18:02,633
Bye.

389
00:18:05,653 --> 00:18:07,643
I'm so excited.

390
00:18:10,153 --> 00:18:14,333
Starting a job while you're here
feels significant, doesn't it?

391
00:18:14,333 --> 00:18:15,563
I know.

392
00:18:15,563 --> 00:18:19,243
It was neat that everything
worked out in a timely manner.

393
00:18:19,243 --> 00:18:21,623
Something good must be happening.

394
00:18:21,623 --> 00:18:26,863
[The special first commute feels
like it will be full of good luck]

395
00:18:28,053 --> 00:18:30,863
You get off at 7? 6:30?

396
00:18:30,863 --> 00:18:33,023
- 6:30.
- 6:30?

397
00:18:34,913 --> 00:18:39,263
Do you have to be at work by 10?

398
00:18:39,263 --> 00:18:41,583
Me? I have to be there by 10:30.

399
00:18:41,583 --> 00:18:43,303
Oh, really?

400
00:18:44,163 --> 00:18:48,133
- He has to go to work early.
- He does, right?

401
00:18:48,133 --> 00:18:50,063
- I can just work out.
- Really?

402
00:18:50,063 --> 00:18:52,823
- Wow, he's cool.
- I love it.

403
00:18:52,823 --> 00:18:55,243
He changed.
He didn't give her medicine, either.

404
00:18:55,243 --> 00:18:56,863
[Glancing]

405
00:18:57,873 --> 00:19:02,313
I usually get there 10 or 20 minutes earlier.

406
00:19:02,313 --> 00:19:05,203
I try to be proactive at work.

407
00:19:06,174 --> 00:19:08,610
Aren't you like that, too? I get that sense.

408
00:19:08,610 --> 00:19:10,263
Yeah, I do that.

409
00:19:10,263 --> 00:19:11,853
[His comment makes her feel happy]

410
00:19:11,853 --> 00:19:14,403
I'm always busy on my own.

411
00:19:14,403 --> 00:19:17,663
Their relationship feels more stable.

412
00:19:17,663 --> 00:19:20,103
[Starting to hum naturally]

413
00:19:21,223 --> 00:19:24,853
This is how it feels. Living in Signal House,

414
00:19:24,853 --> 00:19:31,143
going to work on my own, and coming back.

415
00:19:31,143 --> 00:19:33,093
It must've been hard for you.

416
00:19:33,093 --> 00:19:35,593
Going back and forth.

417
00:19:35,593 --> 00:19:39,503
It's not exactly hard.

418
00:19:39,503 --> 00:19:43,823
I just felt a disconnect.

419
00:19:47,163 --> 00:19:48,783
We're going to cook.

420
00:19:48,783 --> 00:19:51,693
Is no one home? Hold on.

421
00:19:51,693 --> 00:19:52,983
What are you making?

422
00:19:52,983 --> 00:19:55,453
- Tuna kimchi stew.
- Tuna kimchi stew?

423
00:19:55,453 --> 00:19:57,493
It's Sunday today. Let's go out.

424
00:19:57,493 --> 00:20:00,083
[He volunteered to drive on the weekend]

425
00:20:00,083 --> 00:20:02,953
- Aren't you tired?
- No, I'm fine.

426
00:20:02,953 --> 00:20:07,713
[He's always nonchalant and quiet]

427
00:20:07,713 --> 00:20:09,453
Right, right.

428
00:20:10,293 --> 00:20:12,563
[They arrive at her work]

429
00:20:12,563 --> 00:20:14,093
Good luck.

430
00:20:14,093 --> 00:20:16,013
- You'll be fine.
- She must be nervous.

431
00:20:16,013 --> 00:20:17,953
- Go get 'em.
- Go get 'em.

432
00:20:17,953 --> 00:20:21,813
She'll come back feeling exhausted.
I hope she's okay.

433
00:20:21,813 --> 00:20:23,753
She's feeling good.

434
00:20:24,663 --> 00:20:27,793
Thank you. Have a nice day.

435
00:20:27,793 --> 00:20:29,023
- See you later.
- Bye.

436
00:20:29,023 --> 00:20:30,763
Have a nice day.

437
00:20:30,763 --> 00:20:33,373
- Don't you need water?
- I'll take it.

438
00:20:33,373 --> 00:20:36,323
- Bye.
- Bye, see you.

439
00:20:36,323 --> 00:20:38,663
Pure. They're so pure.

440
00:20:38,663 --> 00:20:42,133
[How will the pleasant start affect her day?]

441
00:20:43,993 --> 00:20:49,143
[Seong Min is leaving after seeing her off]

442
00:20:49,143 --> 00:20:52,463
Their tones haven't changed,
but it feels a lot more stable.

443
00:20:52,463 --> 00:20:54,963
- I know.
- And there's a bit of excitement, too.

444
00:20:54,963 --> 00:20:57,843
While in Japan, when Seong Min said,

445
00:20:57,843 --> 00:21:00,253
"I hope this moment lasts forever,"

446
00:21:00,253 --> 00:21:03,853
he was expressing a lot more

447
00:21:03,853 --> 00:21:07,363
intense emotions in that one sentence.

448
00:21:07,363 --> 00:21:10,833
And Min Ju must've been a part of it.

449
00:21:10,833 --> 00:21:12,863
He went to work an hour earlier.

450
00:21:12,863 --> 00:21:16,563
- That means he's doing a lot.
- Sure.

451
00:21:16,563 --> 00:21:19,353
- Who wants a Dubai chocolate cookie?
- I do.

452
00:21:19,353 --> 00:21:24,053
Let's tidy up first, Unni. I'll clean up.

453
00:21:26,333 --> 00:21:27,943
Bring it, bring it.

454
00:21:29,453 --> 00:21:31,303
Give me. I'll do it.

455
00:21:32,063 --> 00:21:34,263
The sausage rolled on it.

456
00:21:36,003 --> 00:21:37,893
- Should I scrub it?
- Yes.

457
00:21:38,753 --> 00:21:40,443
Scrub it hard.

458
00:21:41,373 --> 00:21:43,663
Do you want sunflower seeds?

459
00:21:43,663 --> 00:21:45,313
[Yum]

460
00:21:45,313 --> 00:21:48,243
- She puts sunflower seeds in his mouth.
- So Yun's here.

461
00:21:48,243 --> 00:21:50,823
- Jun Hyeon is here, too.
- Flip every ten or five seconds.

462
00:21:50,823 --> 00:21:52,623
It's so cute how she's tiptoeing to look.

463
00:21:52,623 --> 00:21:54,543
No, I spilled something.

464
00:21:54,543 --> 00:21:57,403
- I did, too.
- Me, too.

465
00:22:00,473 --> 00:22:01,793
[Gyu Ri came down to the kitchen]

466
00:22:01,793 --> 00:22:03,673
Hold on, hold on a second.

467
00:22:03,673 --> 00:22:05,423
What's going on?

468
00:22:06,303 --> 00:22:08,113
In two days?

469
00:22:12,603 --> 00:22:15,333
- Nice combination.
- Of course.

470
00:22:16,293 --> 00:22:19,093
Is there something I can do? Is there more?

471
00:22:19,093 --> 00:22:20,443
[Leaning]

472
00:22:22,063 --> 00:22:25,343
- It's cold.
- Sorry. Sorry.

473
00:22:31,833 --> 00:22:35,003
- Unni, you said you ate, right?
- Yes.

474
00:22:39,863 --> 00:22:42,683
[Wiping]

475
00:22:45,473 --> 00:22:48,223
[Gyu Ri is looking around the library]

476
00:22:48,223 --> 00:22:49,733
[There is a postcard in her book]

477
00:22:49,733 --> 00:22:52,663
Huh? There's a postcard here, too.

478
00:22:58,813 --> 00:23:03,323
[What do you think love is?
Be as specific as possible]

479
00:23:03,323 --> 00:23:05,103
[Seo Won asked the question]

480
00:23:05,103 --> 00:23:07,783
Seo Won keeps trying.

481
00:23:09,163 --> 00:23:11,363
He had a lot on his mind
after the movie yesterday.

482
00:23:11,363 --> 00:23:13,483
[Can't keep her eyes off it]

483
00:23:14,613 --> 00:23:18,903
[Looking around]

484
00:23:19,463 --> 00:23:24,303
[Carefully taking the postcard]

485
00:23:25,883 --> 00:23:28,923
- Are you going to eat?
- Should I?

486
00:23:30,853 --> 00:23:32,813
[Hearing noises outside]

487
00:23:32,813 --> 00:23:34,773
So Yun is so funny.

488
00:23:35,773 --> 00:23:37,953
- Get some honey.
- She's hiding.

489
00:23:37,953 --> 00:23:40,343
You're not puffy at all anymore.

490
00:23:40,343 --> 00:23:42,113
Your eyelids are sunken.

491
00:23:42,113 --> 00:23:43,023
[Opening wide]

492
00:23:45,233 --> 00:23:47,533
Is it because I did the dishes?

493
00:23:47,533 --> 00:23:49,203
Mine are, too.

494
00:23:49,203 --> 00:23:52,163
Your eyes look different today.

495
00:23:54,663 --> 00:23:57,573
You're like a sassy cat.

496
00:23:57,573 --> 00:24:00,273
What animal do you look like? Deer?

497
00:24:00,273 --> 00:24:03,793
- I don't know. No one has ever told me.
- A deer?

498
00:24:03,793 --> 00:24:06,883
I think a deer should have big, twinkly eyes.

499
00:24:06,883 --> 00:24:09,723
- She does look like a deer.
- She's a deer. She is.

500
00:24:09,723 --> 00:24:12,023
Reindeer?

501
00:24:12,023 --> 00:24:13,883
[Definitely a reindeer]

502
00:24:13,883 --> 00:24:17,693
- Water deer?
- She has a poetic vibe.

503
00:24:17,693 --> 00:24:19,643
Dog.

504
00:24:19,643 --> 00:24:21,903
- A doggy face.
- To my face?

505
00:24:21,903 --> 00:24:23,593
[Trying to look like a dog?]

506
00:24:24,493 --> 00:24:27,193
He keeps making her heart flutter.

507
00:24:28,943 --> 00:24:31,193
Have you tried reading those books?

508
00:24:31,193 --> 00:24:32,963
Those books over there?

509
00:24:33,963 --> 00:24:36,173
Should we try reading the one at the end?

510
00:24:36,173 --> 00:24:39,003
Whose book? Hamster's?

511
00:24:39,003 --> 00:24:42,153
- No, Yellow's.
- My gosh!

512
00:24:42,153 --> 00:24:44,493
Yellow's?

