00:38:52,503 --> 00:38:56,143
[The tea room is empty after
Wu Yeol and Yu Gyeong left]

773
00:38:58,933 --> 00:39:01,093
[Curious]

774
00:39:01,093 --> 00:39:03,393
So nice.

775
00:39:03,393 --> 00:39:05,893
I looked like this the whole time?

776
00:39:07,543 --> 00:39:11,623
I'll redo the makeup. I look too tired.

777
00:39:13,333 --> 00:39:15,223
[Min Ju is getting ready
to enter the tea room]

778
00:39:19,173 --> 00:39:20,613
What are you up to?

779
00:39:21,653 --> 00:39:22,963
What do you want to do?

780
00:39:22,963 --> 00:39:25,273
- "What do you want to do?"
- Let's watch a movie, too.

781
00:39:25,273 --> 00:39:28,903
They watched a movie in here.

782
00:39:28,903 --> 00:39:33,023
It's so nice.
This is what they've been up to.

783
00:39:33,023 --> 00:39:34,403
It feels too sexy in here.

784
00:39:34,403 --> 00:39:37,533
- What are you saying? Come on.
- It's too dark in here.

785
00:39:37,533 --> 00:39:40,543
That's how you watch a movie.

786
00:39:40,543 --> 00:39:41,593
Want me to close the door?

787
00:39:41,593 --> 00:39:43,483
[Seong Min and Min Ju overtook the team room]

788
00:39:44,333 --> 00:39:46,163
It was under my account.

789
00:39:46,163 --> 00:39:48,573
- Is this yours?
- Yes.

790
00:39:48,573 --> 00:39:50,753
I set it up a while ago.

791
00:39:50,753 --> 00:39:53,553
- How was today?
- He should ask. It was her first day.

792
00:39:53,553 --> 00:39:55,383
I felt nervous.

793
00:39:56,553 --> 00:39:59,443
I respect Wu Yeol for this.

794
00:39:59,443 --> 00:40:01,513
He's making himself clear now.

795
00:40:01,513 --> 00:40:04,333
He is re-establishing the order.

796
00:40:04,333 --> 00:40:07,843
Wu Yeol and Yu Gyeong made the
best use of the tea room.

797
00:40:07,843 --> 00:40:12,773
That's a place where a couple
is announcing themselves.

798
00:40:12,773 --> 00:40:14,363
The movie didn't matter.

799
00:40:14,363 --> 00:40:17,773
They were just enjoying the vibe.

800
00:40:17,773 --> 00:40:19,353
They didn't watch the movie.

801
00:40:19,353 --> 00:40:23,533
Wu Yeol has a bit of a bad boy image.

802
00:40:23,533 --> 00:40:26,843
People say we live
to correct misunderstandings.

803
00:40:26,843 --> 00:40:30,623
I think I owe him an apology.

804
00:40:30,623 --> 00:40:33,563
- And wasn't that so So Yun?
- It really was.

805
00:40:33,563 --> 00:40:38,183
She expressed her jealousy playfully.

806
00:40:38,183 --> 00:40:41,723
What she did was passable as a joke.

807
00:40:41,723 --> 00:40:44,173
I know. She actually lifted the mood.

808
00:40:44,173 --> 00:40:46,843
And Gyu Ri happened to get in between that.

809
00:40:46,843 --> 00:40:51,023
It couldn't have been
a pleasant moment for her.

810
00:40:51,023 --> 00:40:53,433
I know. It was her favorite book, too.

811
00:40:53,433 --> 00:40:57,343
That might not be why they chose the movie.

812
00:40:57,343 --> 00:41:00,703
But she might think they did it to show her.

813
00:41:00,703 --> 00:41:02,743
I see why she would think that.

814
00:41:02,743 --> 00:41:05,413
So Yun said he's treating her coldly,

815
00:41:05,413 --> 00:41:07,963
not to give her false hope.

816
00:41:07,963 --> 00:41:11,723
She might think he is
doing the same thing to her.

817
00:41:11,723 --> 00:41:16,323
And Seo Won dressed up and
gifted the flowers to the ladies.

818
00:41:16,323 --> 00:41:19,013
He came running up after
seeing Gyu Ri stepping out.

819
00:41:19,013 --> 00:41:21,303
He wanted to give the other ladies inside.

820
00:41:21,303 --> 00:41:24,633
He wore the coat
to give it to Gyu Ri outside.

821
00:41:24,633 --> 00:41:25,703
[So sweet]

822
00:41:25,703 --> 00:41:27,493
- I agree.
- I'm impressed.

823
00:41:27,493 --> 00:41:28,853
He's thoughtful.

824
00:41:28,853 --> 00:41:31,963
[The day after the stormy night]

825
00:41:33,433 --> 00:41:35,983
Looks so tasty.

826
00:41:37,993 --> 00:41:40,663
- Those are cute French toasts.
- Looks tasty.

827
00:41:40,663 --> 00:41:44,563
[Min Ju is preparing breakfast]

828
00:41:52,453 --> 00:41:54,213
You got ready so quickly.

829
00:41:54,213 --> 00:41:55,803
How did you know?

830
00:41:55,803 --> 00:41:58,493
- I struggled to wake up.
- You did?

831
00:41:58,493 --> 00:42:00,613
- Looks good, right?
- It does.

832
00:42:00,613 --> 00:42:02,503
I wanted to take it to go,

833
00:42:02,503 --> 00:42:05,453
but we don't have any disposable plates.

834
00:42:05,453 --> 00:42:07,853
- Isn't it tasty?
- How did you make it?

835
00:42:07,853 --> 00:42:09,863
Didn't I do a good job?

836
00:42:09,863 --> 00:42:11,253
[Jun Hyeon and Min Ju go to work together]

837
00:42:11,253 --> 00:42:14,483
He must be driving her to work.

838
00:42:14,483 --> 00:42:16,543
- Do you have lunch outside?
- Yes.

839
00:42:16,543 --> 00:42:18,033
[Taking a carpool photo]

840
00:42:18,033 --> 00:42:20,743
These two look good together, too.

841
00:42:23,223 --> 00:42:26,733
Did you tell Seong Min to take today off?

842
00:42:26,733 --> 00:42:28,053
Yes.

843
00:42:28,053 --> 00:42:29,933
- Was he happy?
- Yes.

844
00:42:39,153 --> 00:42:40,593
[Thinking]

845
00:42:40,593 --> 00:42:44,773
I think you'll be too tired
to go to work an hour earlier.

846
00:42:44,773 --> 00:42:48,333
Doing that every day
will be too much for you.

847
00:42:48,333 --> 00:42:51,583
- What do we do, then?
- That answer...

848
00:42:52,473 --> 00:42:55,373
Jun Hyeon offered to drive me.

849
00:42:55,373 --> 00:42:57,243
If you're too tired.

850
00:42:59,263 --> 00:43:01,473
Should I suggest taking turns?

851
00:43:04,313 --> 00:43:08,373
She's reminded that
he doesn't like her that much.

852
00:43:08,373 --> 00:43:10,173
[She seems lost in thought]

853
00:43:16,663 --> 00:43:18,553
I cried...

854
00:43:19,653 --> 00:43:23,043
I cried at work once. I never do that.

855
00:43:23,043 --> 00:43:27,253
But I suddenly felt like crying, strangely.

856
00:43:28,133 --> 00:43:31,703
I find relationships like this
very stressful.

857
00:43:34,773 --> 00:43:40,993
I think I've been afraid
to hurt someone's feelings.

858
00:43:40,993 --> 00:43:44,523
But I'll end up doing that eventually.

859
00:43:47,913 --> 00:43:51,543
What would I have done
if the situation were normal?

860
00:43:51,543 --> 00:43:56,243
If the situation were normal,

861
00:43:57,693 --> 00:44:00,793
I would have cut her off.

862
00:44:02,823 --> 00:44:04,023
Huh?

863
00:44:05,023 --> 00:44:07,443
If the situation were normal,

864
00:44:08,633 --> 00:44:11,003
I wouldn't have seen Yu Gyeong.

865
00:44:11,003 --> 00:44:13,463
Because...

866
00:44:14,543 --> 00:44:17,413
You worked up your courage for me.

867
00:44:25,523 --> 00:44:28,023
[Headache]

868
00:44:30,993 --> 00:44:33,963
I feel like it won't be easy.

869
00:44:37,183 --> 00:44:41,563
Is this a place that could be fun?

870
00:44:41,563 --> 00:44:44,583
The back and forth...

871
00:44:44,583 --> 00:44:47,293
There is a lot of back and forth, right?

872
00:44:50,183 --> 00:44:52,393
What will you have for lunch?

873
00:44:52,393 --> 00:44:54,223
- This place is good.
- Yes, I've been there.

874
00:44:54,223 --> 00:44:56,953
Have you? Whoa.

875
00:44:56,953 --> 00:45:00,003
You're a foodie. You must know good places.

876
00:45:00,003 --> 00:45:03,113
Of course. I always look them up.
We live to eat.

877
00:45:03,113 --> 00:45:04,723
Really?

878
00:45:04,723 --> 00:45:08,663
[Not great, but not a bad way
to start the day]

879
00:45:08,663 --> 00:45:10,093
[Unfortunate]

880
00:45:10,093 --> 00:45:12,963
- It's heartbreaking.
- It is for Min Ju.

881
00:45:12,963 --> 00:45:16,623
Seong Min must have thought
he should still tell her.

882
00:45:16,623 --> 00:45:18,393
Regardless of what he meant,

883
00:45:18,393 --> 00:45:21,883
I'm not sure if he needed to tell her.

884
00:45:21,883 --> 00:45:24,303
- In the tea room.
- It was a hard thing to bring up.

885
00:45:24,303 --> 00:45:27,343
I think he thought it'd be better
to be honest with her.

886
00:45:27,343 --> 00:45:31,493
He can't be lovey-dovey with Min Ju
and approach Yu Gyeong at the same time.

887
00:45:31,493 --> 00:45:32,763
Because he's going to.

888
00:45:32,763 --> 00:45:35,453
He warned her in a way.

889
00:45:35,453 --> 00:45:36,993
Right.

890
00:45:39,163 --> 00:45:40,313
Yu Gyeong.

891
00:45:40,313 --> 00:45:43,553
[Yu Gyeong is returning home]

892
00:45:46,363 --> 00:45:50,323
- Huh? When did you get here?
- Just now.

893
00:45:55,703 --> 00:45:56,943
[Running]

894
00:45:59,023 --> 00:46:00,063
The postcard?

895
00:46:00,063 --> 00:46:01,673
[Taking a postcard quietly]

896
00:46:04,343 --> 00:46:08,483
[Hiding Seong Min's postcard]

897
00:46:11,043 --> 00:46:13,023
[Thinking]

898
00:46:13,023 --> 00:46:16,223
I would've requested it tomorrow...

899
00:46:16,223 --> 00:46:17,503
[They had their first date in Japan]

900
00:46:17,503 --> 00:46:20,543
if I had known it'd be so short.

901
00:46:20,543 --> 00:46:23,873
[While preparing a meal a week ago]

902
00:46:27,963 --> 00:46:29,643
[Concerned]

903
00:46:29,643 --> 00:46:34,403
[Not to hurt Min Ju's feelings,]

904
00:46:34,403 --> 00:46:36,833
[she left the kitchen]

905
00:46:40,243 --> 00:46:41,843
Hold on. What's this?

906
00:46:41,843 --> 00:46:44,263
[Seong Min sent her a postcard last night]

907
00:46:44,263 --> 00:46:46,563
Seong Min wrote her.

908
00:46:48,963 --> 00:46:51,773
This is very public.

909
00:46:52,723 --> 00:46:55,103
I should check later.

910
00:47:01,273 --> 00:47:03,553
- Hamster.
- Wu Yeol was jealous.

911
00:47:03,553 --> 00:47:09,753
[Sending a reply after a lot of thinking]

912
00:47:13,043 --> 00:47:14,203
[Running again]

913
00:47:14,203 --> 00:47:16,223
I wonder what she wrote.

914
00:47:17,303 --> 00:47:21,483
[How does Yu Gyeong feel right now?]

915
00:47:22,443 --> 00:47:24,113
What's that?

916
00:47:26,123 --> 00:47:28,713
The eggs were supposed to be soft and loose.

917
00:47:28,713 --> 00:47:30,983
It's okay. Just break them up.

918
00:47:30,983 --> 00:47:32,993
[Yu Gyeong, So Yun,
and Seo Won are making dinner]

919
00:47:32,993 --> 00:47:35,753
I should cut the pork belly
into small pieces, right?

920
00:47:35,753 --> 00:47:39,213
Yeah, smaller than that.

921
00:47:40,383 --> 00:47:42,473
- Hi.
- Hi.

922
00:47:42,473 --> 00:47:44,433
[Min Ju is home after work]

923
00:47:44,433 --> 00:47:47,003
Unni, this is for you.

924
00:47:47,003 --> 00:47:48,693
Have you all had dinner?

925
00:47:48,693 --> 00:47:50,883
- No, not yet.
- We haven't eaten yet.

926
00:47:50,883 --> 00:47:52,163
These are not leftovers. They're fresh.

927
00:47:52,163 --> 00:47:55,123
Really? Looks so good.

928
00:47:55,123 --> 00:47:56,683
Does everyone want a drink?

929
00:47:56,683 --> 00:47:59,863
- He's picking up something.
- He's getting beer, right?

930
00:47:59,863 --> 00:48:03,253
- Get about 30 cans.
- I'll get beer and some snacks.

931
00:48:03,253 --> 00:48:06,343
- It's on me.
- Let me pay.

932
00:48:06,343 --> 00:48:08,033
- Did work go well?
- Yes.

933
00:48:08,033 --> 00:48:11,663
What? Why are you so down?

934
00:48:11,663 --> 00:48:13,473
It's because I haven't eaten.

935
00:48:13,473 --> 00:48:16,413
- Did you not eat at all today?
- I did.

936
00:48:18,933 --> 00:48:20,503
[Seong Min sees the postcard]

937
00:48:20,503 --> 00:48:22,023
He saw it.

938
00:48:23,103 --> 00:48:26,203
[I'm full of contradictions]

939
00:48:26,203 --> 00:48:29,223
"I'm full of contradictions"?

940
00:48:29,223 --> 00:48:31,493
That could give him the wrong idea.

941
00:48:37,743 --> 00:48:39,293
[Sigh]

942
00:48:45,913 --> 00:48:48,593
[What does her response mean?]

943
00:48:54,683 --> 00:48:57,563
You want a non-alcoholic one?

944
00:48:57,563 --> 00:49:02,933
[The men are picking up beer]

945
00:49:03,693 --> 00:49:05,183
Do you know where it is?

946
00:49:05,183 --> 00:49:07,873
It's within walking distance.

947
00:49:09,563 --> 00:49:11,343
Yu Gyeong must feel conflicted.

948
00:49:11,343 --> 00:49:14,983
[For some reason,
she feels guilty toward her]

949
00:49:17,373 --> 00:49:19,053
"I'm full of contradictions."

950
00:49:19,053 --> 00:49:21,893
She's happy, but she also feels anxious?

951
00:49:21,893 --> 00:49:26,353
She even cried, but she still chose him.

952
00:49:26,353 --> 00:49:29,033
I think that's why she said that.

953
00:49:29,033 --> 00:49:31,983
I don't think she meant it
as a message for Seong Min.

954
00:49:31,983 --> 00:49:34,063
But how would Seong Min take it?

955
00:49:34,063 --> 00:49:35,603
- Don't get the wrong idea.
- I know.

956
00:49:35,603 --> 00:49:39,093
Seong Min might think he has a chance.

957
00:49:39,093 --> 00:49:42,063
I think he would think that.

958
00:49:50,503 --> 00:49:53,743
This was off your list. I hope it's tasty.

959
00:49:53,743 --> 00:49:55,333
I think it will be.

960
00:49:55,333 --> 00:49:57,403
Beer and snacks. Snacks and jellies.

961
00:49:57,403 --> 00:50:00,273
We had tons of snacks. Are they gone?

962
00:50:07,053 --> 00:50:08,933
It's complicated.

963
00:50:15,063 --> 00:50:18,653
[Wu Yeol is returning home]

964
00:50:19,193 --> 00:50:21,093
- Hi.
- Hello.

965
00:50:21,093 --> 00:50:23,663
- Is there soup?
- Yes, there is.

966
00:50:23,663 --> 00:50:27,263
- So Yun sprung out of her seat.
- Hi, good work today.

967
00:50:27,263 --> 00:50:29,043
- Did you eat?
- We're about to.

968
00:50:29,043 --> 00:50:30,643
Everyone went to get beer.

969
00:50:30,643 --> 00:50:33,603
Why are you eating so late?

970
00:50:33,603 --> 00:50:35,893
Because somebody wasn't home yet.

971
00:50:35,893 --> 00:50:38,483
[So Yun is getting food for Wu Yeol]

972
00:50:47,233 --> 00:50:50,293
[After checking himself in the mirror]

973
00:50:50,293 --> 00:50:52,703
[Wu Yeol is heading to the kitchen]

974
00:50:52,703 --> 00:50:54,603
What's for dinner tonight?

975
00:50:56,263 --> 00:50:59,323
- Pork belly kimchi...
- Stir fry?

976
00:50:59,323 --> 00:51:01,793
cheese fried rice.

977
00:51:01,793 --> 00:51:03,473
Looks good.

978
00:51:03,473 --> 00:51:04,773
You can have all this.

979
00:51:04,773 --> 00:51:06,343
- Really?
- Yes.

980
00:51:06,343 --> 00:51:09,193
- Who made all this?
- Unni made the fried rice.

981
00:51:09,193 --> 00:51:12,193
And I made the egg drop soup all on my own.

982
00:51:12,193 --> 00:51:14,233
- Really?
- Yes.

983
00:51:14,233 --> 00:51:15,423
Are you sure?

984
00:51:15,423 --> 00:51:16,643
[Naturally, having a private conversation]

985
00:51:16,643 --> 00:51:20,493
- Is everyone back?
- Yes, except for Gyu Ri.

986
00:51:21,593 --> 00:51:25,033
I'm glad you came in time for dinner.

987
00:51:28,143 --> 00:51:29,913
It's getting cold.

988
00:51:29,913 --> 00:51:32,943
Thank you for cooking.

989
00:51:37,003 --> 00:51:38,513
[Bitter]

990
00:51:38,513 --> 00:51:40,993
What's up with that expression?

991
00:51:40,993 --> 00:51:42,593
You look different.

992
00:51:43,433 --> 00:51:46,033
I got my hair done today.

993
00:51:47,823 --> 00:51:49,073
She's bothered.

994
00:51:49,073 --> 00:51:52,283
- It doesn't look the same, right?
- It looks a bit brown.

995
00:51:52,283 --> 00:51:54,753
I didn't dye it at all.

996
00:51:56,343 --> 00:52:00,503
You cut a lot off at the bottom.

997
00:52:00,503 --> 00:52:02,633
Quite a bit.

998
00:52:02,633 --> 00:52:05,833
I just cleaned it up a bit.

999
00:52:07,353 --> 00:52:10,263
He's making his position clear.

1000
00:52:10,263 --> 00:52:13,113
- It's nice.
- Really?

1001
00:52:17,173 --> 00:52:18,943
It might be cruel, but it's a good thing.

1002
00:52:18,943 --> 00:52:20,613
You're back.

1003
00:52:20,613 --> 00:52:23,323
Everyone's back one by one.

1004
00:52:23,323 --> 00:52:27,543
- We can finally eat.
- Let's all eat now.

1005
00:52:27,543 --> 00:52:31,643
- I'm about to pass out.
- It's past nine, but no one has eaten.

1006
00:52:31,643 --> 00:52:35,903
[After the late dinner]

1007
00:52:37,283 --> 00:52:38,953
You should go rest.

1008
00:52:38,953 --> 00:52:40,723
I felt lonely yesterday.

1009
00:52:40,723 --> 00:52:42,013
- Yesterday?
- Yes.

1010
00:52:42,013 --> 00:52:43,573
- Did you do the dishes yesterday?
- Yes.

1011
00:52:43,573 --> 00:52:45,583
Go rest now.

1012
00:52:45,583 --> 00:52:47,703
I will, but...

1013
00:52:48,703 --> 00:52:50,833
- Is there more on top?
- I'll empty it.

1014
00:52:50,833 --> 00:52:52,773
I'll empty the top rack.

1015
00:52:56,993 --> 00:52:59,163
[Seong Min is grabbing a beer]

1016
00:53:05,233 --> 00:53:07,163
[Glancing]

1017
00:53:07,163 --> 00:53:09,993
[Heading to the living room
where Yu Gyeong is]

1018
00:53:11,083 --> 00:53:12,363
Where is everyone else?

1019
00:53:12,363 --> 00:53:15,653
The girls are coming down soon.

1020
00:53:20,213 --> 00:53:23,223
What time do you leave work?
I mean, leave school?

1021
00:53:23,223 --> 00:53:26,163
Come on.

1022
00:53:26,163 --> 00:53:29,303
I came back around six today.

1023
00:53:30,283 --> 00:53:33,983
The class ended at one.

1024
00:53:33,983 --> 00:53:36,593
Do you want to go out for dinner on Friday?

1025
00:53:36,593 --> 00:53:38,593
- Out?
- Yes.

1026
00:53:38,593 --> 00:53:41,793
Don't you go to school... I mean, work?

1027
00:53:41,793 --> 00:53:44,863
I do. I can leave early.

1028
00:53:44,863 --> 00:53:47,933
Around 6 or 6:30?

1029
00:53:47,933 --> 00:53:49,333
- Is that too late?
- Around then?

1030
00:53:49,333 --> 00:53:52,693
I'll try to convince them.

1031
00:53:52,693 --> 00:53:55,763
I have something important. Please let me go.

1032
00:53:55,763 --> 00:53:57,873
I guess he wants to give it a try.

1033
00:53:57,873 --> 00:54:01,223
- What do you want to eat?
- He has decided.

1034
00:54:04,123 --> 00:54:05,153
[Laughs]

1035
00:54:06,273 --> 00:54:08,153
I don't know.

1036
00:54:08,153 --> 00:54:09,693
You're all done.

1037
00:54:12,383 --> 00:54:15,493
- I'll go now.
- Okay.

1038
00:54:15,493 --> 00:54:16,903
Beef?

1039
00:54:18,363 --> 00:54:21,563
- Is that too...
- That's...

1040
00:54:23,713 --> 00:54:25,893
I mean...

1041
00:54:25,893 --> 00:54:29,413
you get it at a fancy place.

1042
00:54:29,413 --> 00:54:34,433
- I haven't been to places like that often.
- Me, neither.

1043
00:54:37,453 --> 00:54:41,693
I just wanted to go out on a date with you.

1044
00:54:43,973 --> 00:54:46,823
[Wu Yeol enters the living room]

1045
00:54:47,413 --> 00:54:48,903
Is it good?

1046
00:54:50,123 --> 00:54:53,073
[Sitting next to Yu Gyeong naturally]

1047
00:54:54,423 --> 00:54:57,503
[Seong Min has a lot to think about]

1048
00:54:59,093 --> 00:55:01,613
Min Ju doesn't feel great, either.

1049
00:55:03,323 --> 00:55:05,213
[Getting up]

1050
00:55:12,633 --> 00:55:15,763
- What are you up to?
- I was folding towels.

1051
00:55:15,763 --> 00:55:18,153
- I could've joined you.
- No, stay in bed.

1052
00:55:18,153 --> 00:55:21,523
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

1053
00:55:21,523 --> 00:55:23,903
What are you sorry about?

1054
00:55:23,903 --> 00:55:26,973
It's my first time folding them here.

1055
00:55:26,973 --> 00:55:31,403
I've been too... I can't muster the energy.

1056
00:55:32,413 --> 00:55:34,823
Because of work? Or are you
worried about something?

1057
00:55:34,823 --> 00:55:38,703
I think the stress is finally hitting me.

1058
00:55:38,703 --> 00:55:42,823
Of course, she's stressed.
Look what her crush is doing.

1059
00:55:44,533 --> 00:55:48,293
Isn't his feeling subsiding?
I thought they were.

1060
00:55:48,293 --> 00:55:51,443
They probably have
because Yu Gyeong has decided.

1061
00:55:51,443 --> 00:55:53,653
Everyone knows by now.

1062
00:55:55,863 --> 00:55:57,803
Should we go downstairs?

1063
00:55:57,803 --> 00:56:00,313
- I'm not sure if I can.
- Gosh.

1064
00:56:00,313 --> 00:56:03,333
- Why?
- I have no confidence.

1065
00:56:03,333 --> 00:56:06,043
Seo Won, want some chocolate?

1066
00:56:06,043 --> 00:56:08,163
You gave me these yesterday.

1067
00:56:11,063 --> 00:56:12,983
Are you good at this?

1068
00:56:12,983 --> 00:56:14,593
Of course, I am.

1069
00:56:17,593 --> 00:56:19,633
How many times have you done it so far?

1070
00:56:19,633 --> 00:56:22,363
- I'm just getting started.
- Okay.

1071
00:56:22,363 --> 00:56:25,453
[The bottle flipping game suddenly starts]

1072
00:56:25,453 --> 00:56:26,763
Make a wish.

1073
00:56:26,763 --> 00:56:28,573
- A wish?
- A wish.

1074
00:56:28,573 --> 00:56:29,993
Sounds good.

1075
00:56:34,123 --> 00:56:35,113
[Min Ju succeeds]

1076
00:56:35,113 --> 00:56:36,573
She did it.

1077
00:56:37,443 --> 00:56:39,213
[Victory ballet dance]

1078
00:56:39,213 --> 00:56:41,583
Why suddenly a ballet?

1079
00:56:41,583 --> 00:56:44,433
- So cute.
- I'm not done.

1080
00:56:47,803 --> 00:56:50,523
- How long are you dancing?
- I feel amazing.

1081
00:56:50,523 --> 00:56:53,303
- Did you do it in one go?
- Yes.

1082
00:56:53,303 --> 00:56:54,903
Hey...

1083
00:56:54,903 --> 00:56:57,343
- Make my wish come true.
- Do a ballet dance.

1084
00:56:58,293 --> 00:57:01,133
[Another victory ballet dance]

1085
00:57:02,663 --> 00:57:05,263
This is my dance. Look.

1086
00:57:08,883 --> 00:57:10,923
I played two rounds of LoL.

1087
00:57:10,923 --> 00:57:13,063
Huh? Do you play LoL?

1088
00:57:13,063 --> 00:57:14,963
I heard that you do.

1089
00:57:14,963 --> 00:57:17,273
- I told Seo Won.
- Really?

1090
00:57:17,273 --> 00:57:19,873
- That you play the game.
- What's your rank?

1091
00:57:19,873 --> 00:57:23,733
My rank is Emerald. Master 540 points.

1092
00:57:25,143 --> 00:57:27,253
Her ideal man is a good gamer.

1093
00:57:27,253 --> 00:57:29,023
- Really?
- Really.

1094
00:57:29,023 --> 00:57:30,713
Then, I can just take her
to one place on a date.

1095
00:57:30,713 --> 00:57:33,233
How about an internet cafe? What do you say?

1096
00:57:33,233 --> 00:57:34,803
They are so similar.

1097
00:57:34,803 --> 00:57:36,913
Want to try playing together?

1098
00:57:36,913 --> 00:57:39,163
You'll end up texting me that night.
Is that okay?

1099
00:57:39,163 --> 00:57:42,563
[Seo Won's secret weapon,
internet cafe date?]

1100
00:57:42,563 --> 00:57:45,363
When were you most excited today?

1101
00:57:45,363 --> 00:57:49,463
- When Seo Won talked about the game.
- Please, let that happen.

1102
00:57:53,143 --> 00:57:56,053
- Hi.
- Gyu Ri is home.

1103
00:57:56,053 --> 00:57:57,293
Gyu Ri?

1104
00:57:57,293 --> 00:57:58,863
Why are you back so late?

1105
00:57:58,863 --> 00:58:00,923
- Did you eat, Unni?
- Unni.

1106
00:58:00,923 --> 00:58:03,943
Me? Yes, I ate.

1107
00:58:06,183 --> 00:58:09,893
[Gyu Ri is coming to the living room]

1108
00:58:11,333 --> 00:58:14,283
[She is sitting next to Wu Yeol]

1109
00:58:20,993 --> 00:58:23,433
Oh, I got the rose one earlier.

1110
00:58:25,213 --> 00:58:27,383
Did you not get enough sleep?

1111
00:58:27,383 --> 00:58:31,243
- I slept three and a half hours last night.
- You must be so tired.

1112
00:58:31,243 --> 00:58:33,523
- You work so hard.
- I'm so tired.

1113
00:58:33,523 --> 00:58:36,083
- How long did you work for that company?
- For about two years.

1114
00:58:36,083 --> 00:58:39,273
- It's been so long.
- I worked very hard.

1115
00:58:39,273 --> 00:58:41,763
I haven't been sleeping these days.

1116
00:58:41,763 --> 00:58:44,063
- You must be more tired than I am.
- Why is that?

1117
00:58:44,063 --> 00:58:45,883
Because you just started the job.

1118
00:58:45,883 --> 00:58:48,013
You're adjusting to living here
and the new job.

1119
00:58:48,013 --> 00:58:50,523
- I feel more relaxed at work.
- Really?

1120
00:58:50,523 --> 00:58:52,413
- You're so uncomfortable here?
- Yes.

1121
00:58:52,413 --> 00:58:57,323
- It's just too...
- She's having a hard time right now.

1122
00:58:57,323 --> 00:58:59,093
Min Ju.

1123
00:59:00,683 --> 00:59:03,433
- Just one second.
- Why?

1124
00:59:04,623 --> 00:59:09,503
[Gyu Ri and Min Ju are heading to the room]

1125
00:59:10,983 --> 00:59:12,613
I don't think anyone's sleeping tonight.

1126
00:59:12,613 --> 00:59:18,743
What do I do? Unni, I can't see him.

1127
00:59:21,893 --> 00:59:25,623
- What's so funny?
- She's crying in pain.

1128
00:59:25,623 --> 00:59:27,623
I don't even feel the pain anymore.

1129
00:59:27,623 --> 00:59:29,303
She has transcended.

1130
00:59:29,303 --> 00:59:30,913
I think you're so cool.

1131
00:59:30,913 --> 00:59:34,493
I'm not cool. Look at me. I'm in pain.

1132
00:59:34,493 --> 00:59:36,743
How was today?

1133
00:59:36,743 --> 00:59:39,093
- Me?
- Yes, how was today?

1134
00:59:39,093 --> 00:59:41,443
Who was all home today, and how was it?

1135
00:59:41,443 --> 00:59:44,183
Everyone gathered except for you.

1136
00:59:44,183 --> 00:59:47,453
- We all ate together.
- Since dinner?

1137
00:59:49,313 --> 00:59:53,803
How many women can go all in on the
man who likes someone else?

1138
00:59:53,803 --> 00:59:55,243
Two?

1139
00:59:56,013 --> 00:59:57,513
Come on!

1140
00:59:57,513 --> 01:00:01,553
- She's going to cry now.
- Her situation is different than mine.

1141
01:00:01,553 --> 01:00:03,283
- How is it different?
- Hers is way better.

1142
01:00:03,283 --> 01:00:06,233
How is it way better? Look at him.

1143
01:00:06,233 --> 01:00:10,613
Come on. He's obviously into Yu Gyeong.

1144
01:00:10,613 --> 01:00:14,723
Whenever she smiles,
he goes like "hee hee hee."

1145
01:00:14,723 --> 01:00:17,613
- He loves it.
- So funny.

1146
01:00:19,633 --> 01:00:23,803
I can tell that Seong Min is not
as into Yu Gyeong anymore.

1147
01:00:23,803 --> 01:00:26,013
- Me, too. Me, too.
- Really?

1148
01:00:26,013 --> 01:00:28,593
Look at her. She's smiling again.

1149
01:00:28,593 --> 01:00:32,093
Me, too. I'm serious. I really feel that.

1150
01:00:32,093 --> 01:00:33,623
- Really?
- Yes, I mean it.

1151
01:00:33,623 --> 01:00:34,953
Look how happy she is.

1152
01:00:34,953 --> 01:00:37,893
- He totally changed.
- Yes, he did.

1153
01:00:37,893 --> 01:00:39,363
I can feel it.

1154
01:00:39,363 --> 01:00:41,853
- But carpooling is a big deal.
- I told you.

1155
01:00:41,853 --> 01:00:44,973
It's because when I'm at work afterward,

1156
01:00:44,973 --> 01:00:49,033
I can still sense him the entire time.

1157
01:00:49,033 --> 01:00:54,043
- I keep thinking about him.
- That's sharing everyday life.

1158
01:00:54,043 --> 01:00:59,293
It's so private. He is driving me to work.

1159
01:00:59,293 --> 01:01:02,233
- It does a lot.
- It really did.

1160
01:01:03,813 --> 01:01:05,633
This is hard.

1161
01:01:05,633 --> 01:01:07,823
I thought it would be easy.

1162
01:01:07,823 --> 01:01:09,963
Being here.

1163
01:01:09,963 --> 01:01:12,573
I don't know much, but still.

1164
01:01:17,563 --> 01:01:24,743
Wu Yeol is finally starting to talk to me.

1165
01:01:24,743 --> 01:01:29,903
Really? I wanted to ask you
about how it was today.

1166
01:01:32,453 --> 01:01:37,863
He said I must be sad
that I had even less time.

1167
01:01:37,863 --> 01:01:42,413
You came here later than we did.

1168
01:01:42,413 --> 01:01:46,373
You must feel even sadder.

1169
01:01:47,773 --> 01:01:49,203
Right.

1170
01:01:50,033 --> 01:01:51,683
He said that.

1171
01:01:51,683 --> 01:01:54,383
She's so moved by just that.

1172
01:01:56,863 --> 01:01:59,713
This is your chance, then.

1173
01:01:59,713 --> 01:02:06,993
Chance? I thought it was too late
to change anything now.

1174
01:02:06,993 --> 01:02:08,633
Why?

1175
01:02:09,403 --> 01:02:13,633
Because those two are so decided right now.

1176
01:02:18,823 --> 01:02:20,533
You think?

1177
01:02:26,163 --> 01:02:28,653
They are so firm.

1178
01:02:31,123 --> 01:02:34,443
Why? I don't think they are.

1179
01:02:38,123 --> 01:02:39,803
Should we go downstairs?

1180
01:02:40,723 --> 01:02:41,923
I'll wait for you downstairs.

1181
01:02:41,923 --> 01:02:44,783
Okay, I'll change and join you.

1182
01:02:44,783 --> 01:02:47,503
I can't look sleepy.
I can't be sleepy right now.

1183
01:02:47,503 --> 01:02:50,163
I'm really tired.

1184
01:02:50,163 --> 01:02:53,173
But it's still fun.

1185
01:02:55,313 --> 01:02:57,573
Should I get my hair done again?

1186
01:02:59,123 --> 01:03:01,733
Seong Min will probably-

1187
01:03:03,093 --> 01:03:06,333
He'll try to be honest, probably.

1188
01:03:07,723 --> 01:03:11,233
Who do you like, Unni? Is it Seo Won?

1189
01:03:12,013 --> 01:03:13,413
It's a secret.

1190
01:03:13,413 --> 01:03:16,523
Gyu Ri must be really hard to read.

1191
01:03:18,483 --> 01:03:24,223
[Gyu Ri is coming downstairs after changing]

1192
01:03:24,223 --> 01:03:26,513
- Shouldn't we reveal now?
- Reveal what?

1193
01:03:26,513 --> 01:03:28,533
Our nicknames.

1194
01:03:28,533 --> 01:03:30,463
- Did you do Self Talk?
- No.

1195
01:03:30,463 --> 01:03:33,293
- Yu Gyeong is bothered.
- I just got here.

1196
01:03:33,293 --> 01:03:36,013
I should ask if I can leave early
starting tomorrow.

1197
01:03:36,013 --> 01:03:38,733
I'll tell them that...

1198
01:03:38,733 --> 01:03:41,473
each day is important, starting now.

1199
01:03:41,473 --> 01:03:44,483
- I should tell him that.
- Each day.

1200
01:03:44,483 --> 01:03:46,733
It's true. It really is.

1201
01:03:49,683 --> 01:03:52,433
You think it will change because of that?

1202
01:03:52,433 --> 01:03:53,653
With the time left?

1203
01:03:53,653 --> 01:03:56,083
- Because of the time that's left?
- I can see that happening.

1204
01:03:56,083 --> 01:03:58,593
- I think so.
- That sounds loaded.

1205
01:04:01,473 --> 01:04:03,763
I think you should at least try.

1206
01:04:03,763 --> 01:04:07,093
- Regardless of the outcome.
- That's Seong Min's style.

1207
01:04:07,093 --> 01:04:08,883
[Nodding]

1208
01:04:17,053 --> 01:04:20,683
[What would happen in the remaining time?]

1209
01:04:20,683 --> 01:04:24,063
[A wave of change is coming]

1210
01:04:24,063 --> 01:04:27,363
- It's like we are getting a preview.
- I'm so scared.

1211
01:04:27,363 --> 01:04:31,663
A problem may arise between
Wu Yeol and Yu Gyeong.

1212
01:04:31,663 --> 01:04:35,293
- Something I don't want to imagine.
- That can't happen.

1213
01:04:35,293 --> 01:04:39,473
Yu Gyeong feels anxious even though
Wu Yeol expressed his feelings.

1214
01:04:39,473 --> 01:04:42,683
Considering her past heartaches,

1215
01:04:42,683 --> 01:04:46,703
she might worry he'd change his mind again.

1216
01:04:46,703 --> 01:04:49,813
Because they're in the Signal House.

1217
01:04:49,813 --> 01:04:53,773
Say the strengths of your personality.

1218
01:04:53,773 --> 01:04:56,433
- Okay.
- Say the strength of your personality.

1219
01:04:56,433 --> 01:04:59,013
- Let's go in this order.
- Me first?

1220
01:04:59,013 --> 01:05:00,493
- So funny.
- My personality?

1221
01:05:00,493 --> 01:05:03,883
Hold on. Can we say both
weaknesses and strengths?

1222
01:05:03,883 --> 01:05:07,833
- Okay, let's think about it.
- Weaknesses?

1223
01:05:08,643 --> 01:05:11,513
- I can't think of my strength.
- Me neither.

1224
01:05:11,513 --> 01:05:15,163
- I can only think of my weakness.
- Let's just say one or the other.

1225
01:05:15,163 --> 01:05:18,223
- Sounds good.
- We're learning about each other.

1226
01:05:18,223 --> 01:05:19,503
Gyu Ri.

1227
01:05:19,503 --> 01:05:22,653
Me? I have a weakness.

1228
01:05:22,653 --> 01:05:24,993
- Weakness?
- Yes.

1229
01:05:24,993 --> 01:05:28,423
I can't be certain.

1230
01:05:28,423 --> 01:05:30,543
I get anxious.

1231
01:05:31,623 --> 01:05:33,763
Am I the opposite?

1232
01:05:33,763 --> 01:05:37,053
Read Alain de Botton's
"Status Anxiety," then.

1233
01:05:37,053 --> 01:05:38,353
- I know.
- It's a good one.

1234
01:05:38,353 --> 01:05:40,403
- It's a good book.
- I know.

1235
01:05:40,403 --> 01:05:42,903
I read it three times.

1236
01:05:42,903 --> 01:05:44,533
Okay, okay.

1237
01:05:44,533 --> 01:05:47,493
Weaknesses are important, too.

1238
01:05:48,493 --> 01:05:50,353
I have a strength.

1239
01:05:50,353 --> 01:05:52,953
I'm good at expressing my feelings.

1240
01:05:52,953 --> 01:05:55,963
- That's a huge strength.
- I express gratitude when I feel it.

1241
01:05:55,963 --> 01:05:58,353
I kneel and beg when I feel guilty.

1242
01:05:58,353 --> 01:06:00,583
That's a very rare trait.

1243
01:06:00,583 --> 01:06:03,623
I have a question.
Can you say what you don't mean?

1244
01:06:03,623 --> 01:06:07,153
Can you say thank you
when you don't really feel it?

1245
01:06:07,153 --> 01:06:09,053
I can, but you can tell.

1246
01:06:09,053 --> 01:06:11,603
Me, too. It shows on my face.

1247
01:06:11,603 --> 01:06:15,013
My eyes widen slightly,
but widen a lot when I mean it.

1248
01:06:15,013 --> 01:06:17,403
- The size of your eyes?
- With my eyes.

1249
01:06:17,403 --> 01:06:19,333
I think this is my weakness.

1250
01:06:19,333 --> 01:06:22,183
I can't hide my feelings.

1251
01:06:23,333 --> 01:06:26,853
- Being transparent is good.
- It's both a weakness and a strength.

1252
01:06:26,853 --> 01:06:28,963
You might think of it as a weakness.

1253
01:06:28,963 --> 01:06:33,393
Because it's not good
in a professional setting.

1254
01:06:33,393 --> 01:06:36,783
Someone blames me, but I can't accept it.

1255
01:06:36,783 --> 01:06:38,683
We all know we have to,

1256
01:06:38,683 --> 01:06:42,233
but I can't, and it shows on my face.

1257
01:06:42,233 --> 01:06:43,893
That's a social skill...

1258
01:06:43,893 --> 01:06:44,863
[Teasing]

1259
01:06:44,863 --> 01:06:45,833
[Angry]

1260
01:06:45,833 --> 01:06:47,223
Hey!

1261
01:06:47,223 --> 01:06:50,413
- Sorry.
- Too funny.

1262
01:06:51,183 --> 01:06:54,913
But that's... I see.

1263
01:06:56,003 --> 01:06:57,493
Okay.

1264
01:06:58,453 --> 01:06:59,983
For me...

1265
01:07:01,483 --> 01:07:03,643
I'm honest.

1266
01:07:03,643 --> 01:07:07,003
- Is that a strength?
- Yes, but because of that...

1267
01:07:07,003 --> 01:07:10,543
- That's a weakness and a strength.
- Yes, but I get swayed.

1268
01:07:10,543 --> 01:07:13,023
- It's similar.
- With my emotions.

1269
01:07:16,293 --> 01:07:19,803
I get swayed by others, too.
That happens more.

1270
01:07:21,183 --> 01:07:24,713
Because I accept other people's
feelings honestly, too

1271
01:07:26,763 --> 01:07:29,553
You accept other people's feelings honestly?

1272
01:07:31,293 --> 01:07:33,893
Because I can't fake them,

1273
01:07:33,893 --> 01:07:36,963
I think other people can't, either.

1274
01:07:36,963 --> 01:07:38,143
[She thinks everyone is as honest as she is]

1275
01:07:38,143 --> 01:07:40,453
- That must...
- You think everyone is open.

1276
01:07:40,453 --> 01:07:42,803
That must lead to heartache.

1277
01:07:42,803 --> 01:07:45,373
Right. That's why I get hurt often.

1278
01:07:46,213 --> 01:07:50,023
- I can understand that.
- It's relatable.

1279
01:07:50,023 --> 01:07:53,643
People say I would get scammed often.

1280
01:07:53,643 --> 01:07:56,913
- Because you trust everyone?
- I can see that.

1281
01:07:56,913 --> 01:08:00,463
I think everyone behaves just like I do.

1282
01:08:00,463 --> 01:08:02,343
I got scammed three times.

1283
01:08:02,343 --> 01:08:04,763
You actually have?

1284
01:08:04,763 --> 01:08:06,063
[Laugh]

1285
01:08:06,063 --> 01:08:08,783
I submitted a petition three times.

1286
01:08:08,783 --> 01:08:11,713
I've done that at a police station.

1287
01:08:11,713 --> 01:08:12,913
How about you, Oppa?

1288
01:08:12,913 --> 01:08:17,693
I'm similar, too. I'm honest.

1289
01:08:17,693 --> 01:08:23,713
I think my weakness
is that I'm kind of picky.

1290
01:08:23,713 --> 01:08:26,813
Your taste or preferences?

1291
01:08:26,813 --> 01:08:29,513
- You're detail-oriented.
- I am, and...

1292
01:08:29,513 --> 01:08:33,163
- I think I'm picky.
- Why is that a weakness?

1293
01:08:34,143 --> 01:08:36,083
It also means that you are careful.

1294
01:08:36,083 --> 01:08:39,693
I could only focus on the good things.

1295
01:08:39,693 --> 01:08:44,903
But I start noticing other things negatively.

1296
01:08:44,903 --> 01:08:48,353
- It makes you hesitate?
- Yes, a bit.

1297
01:08:49,593 --> 01:08:53,073
Mine is also a weakness and a strength.

1298
01:08:53,073 --> 01:08:56,483
I tend to read people quickly.

1299
01:08:56,483 --> 01:09:00,443
He really does. I've noticed it myself.

1300
01:09:00,443 --> 01:09:04,243
I think he's pretty smart.

1301
01:09:04,243 --> 01:09:07,303
I want to learn that from him.

1302
01:09:07,303 --> 01:09:09,803
But how is that a weakness?

1303
01:09:09,803 --> 01:09:15,403
It makes me study other people's
behaviors and feelings.

1304
01:09:15,403 --> 01:09:16,943
It's hard on me.

1305
01:09:16,943 --> 01:09:21,293
He can notice things
other people want to hide.

1306
01:09:23,913 --> 01:09:27,123
I have a lot of small flaws.

1307
01:09:27,123 --> 01:09:31,763
I know myself too well. I always think
about what kind of person I am.

1308
01:09:31,763 --> 01:09:35,143
My strength is that I present myself clearly.

1309
01:09:35,143 --> 01:09:39,803
I don't want to hide. Let's say I'm clumsy.

1310
01:09:39,803 --> 01:09:45,413
I just tell people that
without feeling ashamed.

1311
01:09:45,413 --> 01:09:48,993
- You get ashamed easily.
- Well, that's...

1312
01:09:48,993 --> 01:09:53,073
I spilled all the tea
on the second day we met.

1313
01:09:53,073 --> 01:09:54,943
I was embarrassed about that.

1314
01:09:54,943 --> 01:09:56,833
- Do you have a lot of self-respect?
- I think he does.

1315
01:09:56,833 --> 01:09:59,783
I think we have something in common.

1316
01:09:59,783 --> 01:10:04,003
My weakness is that I can say what
people don't want to hear.

1317
01:10:04,003 --> 01:10:06,383
Like, you say you're constipated?

1318
01:10:06,383 --> 01:10:09,343
- That you pooped today or not?
- Not that.

1319
01:10:09,343 --> 01:10:11,293
Oh, come on.

1320
01:10:11,293 --> 01:10:13,033
Have you said such a thing?

1321
01:10:13,033 --> 01:10:16,443
- Not stuff like that.
- There is something I love to do.

1322
01:10:16,443 --> 01:10:20,353
I like reporting my everyday life
to someone I love.

1323
01:10:20,353 --> 01:10:23,353
About who I met, what I did,
and what I'm planning to do.

1324
01:10:23,353 --> 01:10:26,573
I'm going to bed. I woke up. Good morning.

1325
01:10:26,573 --> 01:10:28,803
So cute.

1326
01:10:28,803 --> 01:10:30,863
- You have to say good morning.
- Good night.

1327
01:10:30,863 --> 01:10:34,113
You have to say good morning
with a heart symbol.

1328
01:10:34,113 --> 01:10:35,823
Good night, too.

1329
01:10:35,823 --> 01:10:38,883
You have to add a heart symbol
even after a fight.

1330
01:10:38,883 --> 01:10:43,133
This is what I want to hear.
Details like this.

1331
01:10:43,133 --> 01:10:44,743
You are a true mensch.

1332
01:10:44,743 --> 01:10:46,893
Because it won't be good the next day.

1333
01:10:46,893 --> 01:10:49,693
What if you don't get the heart symbol back?

1334
01:10:49,693 --> 01:10:51,783
That doesn't matter because...

1335
01:10:51,783 --> 01:10:53,513
It doesn't matter? What a man.

1336
01:10:53,513 --> 01:10:56,033
- I'd feel disappointed,
- I'd wait until I get one.

1337
01:10:56,033 --> 01:10:58,073
but I have to do what I have to do.

1338
01:10:58,073 --> 01:11:00,973
I think you'll add a heart
until you get one in return.

1339
01:11:00,973 --> 01:11:02,513
That's right.

1340
01:11:02,513 --> 01:11:06,093
I would call them and demand one.

1341
01:11:06,943 --> 01:11:10,213
- I like details like this. Tell me more.
- It's hard to picture it.

1342
01:11:10,213 --> 01:11:12,103
But people usually reciprocate.

1343
01:11:12,103 --> 01:11:15,393
Don't people do that usually?

1344
01:11:15,393 --> 01:11:17,013
If you're in a relationship?

1345
01:11:17,013 --> 01:11:20,213
We all know how we are in relationships.

1346
01:11:20,213 --> 01:11:25,023
I become so expressive when in relationships.

1347
01:11:25,023 --> 01:11:26,953
That's nice.

1348
01:11:26,953 --> 01:11:31,023
You become so expressive
only to your girlfriend.

1349
01:11:33,323 --> 01:11:35,423
I become mischievous.

1350
01:11:35,423 --> 01:11:37,293
What are you like when you fight?

1351
01:11:37,293 --> 01:11:40,933
- This is so important, honestly.
- I think it's very important.

1352
01:11:40,933 --> 01:11:43,553
Your relationship depends on how you fight.

1353
01:11:43,553 --> 01:11:45,913
I know. First...

1354
01:11:45,913 --> 01:11:48,633
I say I'm sorry.

1355
01:11:48,633 --> 01:11:52,753
- When you fight?
- Yes. I always say sorry first.

1356
01:11:52,753 --> 01:11:54,423
Second, I listen.

1357
01:11:54,423 --> 01:11:55,743
[Curious]

1358
01:11:55,743 --> 01:11:57,433
Since I already said I'm sorry,

1359
01:11:57,433 --> 01:11:59,723
I say, I think such and such about this.

1360
01:11:59,723 --> 01:12:02,463
Third, I ask, "What do you think?"

1361
01:12:02,463 --> 01:12:04,973
Fourth...

1362
01:12:04,973 --> 01:12:07,133
Why are there so many steps?

1363
01:12:08,033 --> 01:12:10,143
I don't want to fight with you.

1364
01:12:10,143 --> 01:12:12,243
I'm not fighting with him.

1365
01:12:12,243 --> 01:12:14,963
He writes a contract before he fights.

1366
01:12:14,963 --> 01:12:16,533
Let's just be friendly.

1367
01:12:16,533 --> 01:12:20,623
[A night where they got to know
each other better]

1368
01:12:20,623 --> 01:12:25,383
[The next day, another night]

1369
01:12:25,383 --> 01:12:29,953
[So Yun returns to the house]

1370
01:12:34,723 --> 01:12:36,813
- Unni!
- What?

1371
01:12:36,813 --> 01:12:39,713
- No one is here!
- Still?

1372
01:12:39,713 --> 01:12:42,343
We're always the ones home.

1373
01:12:42,343 --> 01:12:44,593
What is this?

1374
01:12:44,593 --> 01:12:47,723
- What is this?
- Want a mini boongeoppang?

1375
01:12:47,723 --> 01:12:50,013
Just one. Red bean.

1376
01:12:51,013 --> 01:12:53,753
I love red bean. Thank you.

1377
01:12:53,753 --> 01:12:54,913
[Nom]

1378
01:12:58,533 --> 01:12:59,883
[Big nom]

1379
01:13:00,513 --> 01:13:01,703
[So hot]

1380
01:13:05,503 --> 01:13:06,503
[Ta-da]

1381
01:13:06,503 --> 01:13:08,743
- What is it?
- I bought it.

1382
01:13:08,743 --> 01:13:11,883
- To clean the bathroom?
- Steel wool. No.

1383
01:13:12,883 --> 01:13:14,543
The frying pan.

1384
01:13:15,993 --> 01:13:18,473
[Remembers a conversation]

1385
01:13:19,013 --> 01:13:22,163
Yu Gyeong, what do you do
when you're home alone?

1386
01:13:22,163 --> 01:13:24,313
If I'm here alone?

1387
01:13:24,313 --> 01:13:26,423
I just lie around...

1388
01:13:26,423 --> 01:13:28,083
[Flop]

1389
01:13:30,303 --> 01:13:35,533
Today, I washed the towels.

1390
01:13:35,533 --> 01:13:40,553
I feel so satisfied.
There was a big pile of towels.

1391
01:13:40,553 --> 01:13:48,753
[Filling their time at the house
in their own way]

1392
01:13:48,753 --> 01:13:50,223
[Getting ready to make dinner]

1393
01:13:50,223 --> 01:13:56,073
I'll tell you about making rice
over the past few days.

1394
01:13:56,073 --> 01:13:59,233
Wash the rice about three times.

1395
01:13:59,233 --> 01:14:02,513
The first time I made food here...

1396
01:14:02,513 --> 01:14:06,173
[Day 1]

1397
01:14:06,173 --> 01:14:09,113
[Clumsily made pasta]

1398
01:14:10,983 --> 01:14:13,673
- You studied.
- I had no idea.

1399
01:14:13,673 --> 01:14:15,693
When I did this...

1400
01:14:15,693 --> 01:14:18,133
I think this is just right.

1401
01:14:18,133 --> 01:14:19,653
Can you feel it?

1402
01:14:19,653 --> 01:14:23,763
- You can pick the setting, sticky or fluffy.
- Fluffy.

1403
01:14:23,763 --> 01:14:26,533
[An evening spent together]

1404
01:14:26,533 --> 01:14:30,163
- I'll do that.
- No, it's just a few.

1405
01:14:30,163 --> 01:14:34,243
- Or maybe you can organize those?
- Okay.

1406
01:14:34,243 --> 01:14:37,673
We're such home protectors.

1407
01:14:37,673 --> 01:14:40,453
[Taking care of piled-up chores]

1408
01:14:40,453 --> 01:14:43,503
We should throw out the stuff
in the bathroom.

1409
01:14:44,433 --> 01:14:47,103
There has to be one...

1410
01:14:47,983 --> 01:14:49,883
[Finds it immediately]

1411
01:14:49,883 --> 01:14:52,313
[Already adjusted to living at Signal House]

1412
01:14:52,313 --> 01:14:53,883
Ask, and you shall receive.

1413
01:14:53,883 --> 01:14:57,133
[Wu Yeol returns to the house after work]

1414
01:15:05,303 --> 01:15:07,633
- Oh!
- It's a person.

1415
01:15:09,173 --> 01:15:10,973
Where were you?

1416
01:15:10,973 --> 01:15:13,673
I went to the gym after work.

1417
01:15:13,673 --> 01:15:16,593
I suddenly felt like, if I don't go today...

1418
01:15:16,593 --> 01:15:19,093
You were going to pass out and die?

1419
01:15:19,093 --> 01:15:21,473
- I felt like everything I did
- So Yun sees him.

1420
01:15:21,473 --> 01:15:23,703
would go to waste.

1421
01:15:23,703 --> 01:15:25,983
Should we eat?

1422
01:15:25,983 --> 01:15:28,683
- Tell him the menu.
- Soy sauce eggs with rice.

1423
01:15:28,683 --> 01:15:30,703
I love it.

1424
01:15:30,703 --> 01:15:33,183
- Should we grill meat?
- Meat is good.

1425
01:15:33,183 --> 01:15:36,033
Let's grill some meat. It's three people.

1426
01:15:36,033 --> 01:15:38,763
- I'll grill.
- Getting fancy since it's three people?

1427
01:15:38,763 --> 01:15:40,473
Hey...

1428
01:15:41,993 --> 01:15:43,903
What? What do you want?

1429
01:15:43,903 --> 01:15:46,483
I'm good at making eggs.

1430
01:15:46,483 --> 01:15:48,363
- I'll have that.
- No, I'm having that.

1431
01:15:48,363 --> 01:15:51,543
I worked out today, so I need protein.

1432
01:15:53,383 --> 01:15:55,413
Seven minutes left for the rice.

1433
01:15:55,413 --> 01:15:58,823
[Wu Yeol and Yu Gyeong standing side by side]

1434
01:15:58,823 --> 01:16:00,113
Let's use a lot of oil.

1435
01:16:00,113 --> 01:16:01,463
[Glancing]

1436
01:16:02,543 --> 01:16:06,383
[Seo Won returns home]

1437
01:16:06,383 --> 01:16:07,833
- You're home!
- Hey!

1438
01:16:07,833 --> 01:16:11,813
Why are you so late?
You said you'd come home early.

1439
01:16:11,813 --> 01:16:13,543
Should I grill all of them?

1440
01:16:13,543 --> 01:16:15,463
Yes, let's feast while we're at it.

1441
01:16:15,463 --> 01:16:17,063
Sure, sure.

1442
01:16:17,063 --> 01:16:18,923
We need to run again today...

1443
01:16:18,923 --> 01:16:21,243
Where?

1444
01:16:21,243 --> 01:16:23,463
To where?

1445
01:16:23,463 --> 01:16:24,853
I'm down.

1446
01:16:24,853 --> 01:16:31,263
[They prepare dinner together]

1447
01:16:31,263 --> 01:16:32,973
[Butter for the soy sauce egg rice]

1448
01:16:34,273 --> 01:16:36,393
It's hard.

1449
01:16:36,393 --> 01:16:37,493
Just wait.

1450
01:16:37,493 --> 01:16:38,763
[Grinning]

1451
01:16:39,703 --> 01:16:42,483
You don't trust me?

1452
01:16:42,483 --> 01:16:43,453
[Smooth]

1453
01:16:49,573 --> 01:16:50,963
I didn't see it.

1454
01:16:51,733 --> 01:16:53,413
Actually, I did.

1455
01:16:56,373 --> 01:17:00,013
[Spreading some sesame seeds]

1456
01:17:00,013 --> 01:17:03,643
- Wow, these visuals.
- Looks so good.

1457
01:17:03,643 --> 01:17:05,693
[Pouring the last bit of sesame oil]

1458
01:17:05,693 --> 01:17:08,283
[Savory soy sauce egg rice complete]

1459
01:17:08,993 --> 01:17:11,593
- The butter melted, right?
- There was butter?

1460
01:17:11,593 --> 01:17:13,303
Thank you for the food.

1461
01:17:15,563 --> 01:17:17,143
[A big bite]

1462
01:17:17,143 --> 01:17:18,793
The kimchi is so good.

1463
01:17:22,993 --> 01:17:25,403
The rice is perfect.

1464
01:17:26,413 --> 01:17:28,203
Who made it?

1465
01:17:29,343 --> 01:17:30,813
[The best]

1466
01:17:31,923 --> 01:17:34,993
This is my favorite meal
I've had here so far.

1467
01:17:34,993 --> 01:17:36,593
It's so good.

1468
01:17:37,593 --> 01:17:39,113
So good.

1469
01:17:39,113 --> 01:17:41,433
Who picked the menu?

1470
01:17:41,433 --> 01:17:43,233
Me.

1471
01:17:45,773 --> 01:17:47,323
I guess I was hungry.

1472
01:17:47,323 --> 01:17:49,823
I saw snacks on your bed.

1473
01:17:49,823 --> 01:17:50,983
[Caught red-handed]

1474
01:17:54,293 --> 01:17:57,323
[Big bite]

1475
01:17:57,843 --> 01:17:59,723
[A dance for tastiness]

1476
01:18:01,313 --> 01:18:02,953
[The dance does not stop]

1477
01:18:03,703 --> 01:18:05,563
[So cute]

1478
01:18:14,543 --> 01:18:15,843
So good.

1479
01:18:15,843 --> 01:18:18,463
You're so fun to cook for.

1480
01:18:18,463 --> 01:18:20,173
It's so tasty.

1481
01:18:22,833 --> 01:18:24,353
Don't regret it later. Have plenty.

1482
01:18:24,353 --> 01:18:26,113
I won't regret it.

1483
01:18:26,113 --> 01:18:28,223
I don't make regrettable choices.

1484
01:18:29,533 --> 01:18:31,413
What are you doing?

1485
01:18:31,413 --> 01:18:32,983
I'm going to do the dishes.

1486
01:18:32,983 --> 01:18:34,913
- Getting mentally ready.
- I'll do it with you.

1487
01:18:36,673 --> 01:18:38,383
- Ta-da!
- You bought this?

1488
01:18:38,383 --> 01:18:40,073
- Yes.
- It's war, then.

1489
01:18:40,073 --> 01:18:42,623
We need to do the dishes.

1490
01:18:42,623 --> 01:18:46,053
Let's clean all the sticky stuff today.

1491
01:18:46,053 --> 01:18:49,623
I feel like the air quality is not great.

1492
01:18:49,623 --> 01:18:53,093
[This is when you need an air purifier]

1493
01:18:55,393 --> 01:18:58,093
[The air becomes a lot fresher]

1494
01:19:00,103 --> 01:19:02,193
- You got here at 9:30?
- Yeah.

1495
01:19:02,193 --> 01:19:03,713
That wasn't that long ago.

1496
01:19:03,713 --> 01:19:06,973
[Dishes time after a happy meal]

1497
01:19:06,973 --> 01:19:10,103
Were you okay at work today?

1498
01:19:10,103 --> 01:19:14,013
Today? It was great.
To think about coming home.

1499
01:19:14,013 --> 01:19:18,343
But I went to the gym
to keep myself on my toes.

1500
01:19:18,343 --> 01:19:21,033
For whom?

1501
01:19:23,593 --> 01:19:25,303
What?

1502
01:19:26,273 --> 01:19:28,693
Drinking is a habit now.

1503
01:19:28,693 --> 01:19:32,293
I've never lived like this.

1504
01:19:32,293 --> 01:19:36,453
- I don't know if I can do this.
- You feel pathetic?

1505
01:19:37,283 --> 01:19:39,353
Just enjoy it.

1506
01:19:39,353 --> 01:19:41,473
If not now, when?

1507
01:19:41,473 --> 01:19:42,933
Right.

1508
01:19:44,153 --> 01:19:45,103
[Water splashed on her shirt]

1509
01:19:45,103 --> 01:19:48,253
"Enjoy it. If not now, when?"

1510
01:19:48,253 --> 01:19:50,333
Waterbomb.

1511
01:19:50,333 --> 01:19:53,393
Doesn't it make you happy
to see it get clean?

1512
01:19:53,393 --> 01:19:55,073
That's why I do dishes.

1513
01:19:55,073 --> 01:19:59,343
I'm so thankful we can do dishes right now.

1514
01:19:59,343 --> 01:20:01,323
Let's say one thing
we're thankful for per day.

1515
01:20:01,323 --> 01:20:03,023
I can say fifteen a day.

1516
01:20:03,023 --> 01:20:05,253
- Really?
- Of course.

1517
01:20:05,253 --> 01:20:08,893
Thankful for the steel wool.

1518
01:20:12,253 --> 01:20:17,873
[Gyu Ri returns to the house]

1519
01:20:20,293 --> 01:20:23,163
I'm home!

1520
01:20:23,163 --> 01:20:25,563
Guys...

1521
01:20:28,043 --> 01:20:30,613
I think Gyu Ri is home.

1522
01:20:33,193 --> 01:20:35,493
[Water splashed on his shirt]

1523
01:20:35,493 --> 01:20:37,823
Yu Gyeong-core.

1524
01:20:39,943 --> 01:20:42,873
This is a familiar scene.

1525
01:20:42,873 --> 01:20:44,183
Hello!

1526
01:20:44,183 --> 01:20:46,883
- I'm home.
- Did you eat?

1527
01:20:46,883 --> 01:20:50,313
I did. Where is everyone?

1528
01:20:50,313 --> 01:20:52,823
- I don't know.
- Seo Won unni...

1529
01:20:52,823 --> 01:20:55,023
"Seo Won unni"?

1530
01:20:55,023 --> 01:20:58,733
It's just Seo Won oppa and So Yun unni here.

1531
01:20:58,733 --> 01:21:00,613
I think people are working late.

1532
01:21:00,613 --> 01:21:03,113
Really? Got it.

1533
01:21:03,113 --> 01:21:06,623
[Seo Won and So Yun are talking]

1534
01:21:08,023 --> 01:21:09,573
You're home!

1535
01:21:10,523 --> 01:21:12,133
Hey!

1536
01:21:12,133 --> 01:21:14,243
- Hi.
- So cute.

1537
01:21:14,243 --> 01:21:15,743
I'm so happy.

1538
01:21:15,743 --> 01:21:18,593
Why? Because you're home?

1539
01:21:25,823 --> 01:21:29,383
[A night too good to pass up]

1540
01:21:29,383 --> 01:21:33,053
[Finishing off the day together
in the living room]

1541
01:21:37,533 --> 01:21:39,163
[Chugging]

1542
01:21:45,573 --> 01:21:48,083
They don't even talk.

1543
01:21:48,083 --> 01:21:51,133
Nothing I thought of was there.

1544
01:21:51,133 --> 01:21:57,123
[The air is uncomfortable for some reason]

1545
01:21:57,123 --> 01:22:00,193
Everyone's face hardens when they sit here.

1546
01:22:00,193 --> 01:22:02,433
[Emptying her glass already]

1547
01:22:05,993 --> 01:22:11,093
I was grinning all the way
from the cafe down there.

1548
01:22:11,093 --> 01:22:15,033
I yelled "I'm home!"
on the first floor coming in,

1549
01:22:15,033 --> 01:22:18,793
but the two of them didn't say anything.

1550
01:22:18,793 --> 01:22:21,043
The first floor...

1551
01:22:21,043 --> 01:22:23,473
- Wow, so sad.
- I didn't hear you.

1552
01:22:23,473 --> 01:22:26,913
I said "I'm home!" twice.

1553
01:22:26,913 --> 01:22:30,563
I thought you were talking to someone.

1554
01:22:30,563 --> 01:22:32,693
[A sudden misunderstanding]

1555
01:22:32,693 --> 01:22:34,903
I thought, "Gyu Ri must be home."

1556
01:22:34,903 --> 01:22:37,603
- Someone's here!
- He's actually here.

1557
01:22:37,603 --> 01:22:38,783
[Standing up]

1558
01:22:38,783 --> 01:22:40,963
Hi!

1559
01:22:42,203 --> 01:22:43,753
She came home so late.

1560
01:22:43,753 --> 01:22:45,783
I'm so tired.

1561
01:22:45,783 --> 01:22:47,883
Are you okay?

1562
01:22:49,253 --> 01:22:51,763
[Gyu Ri comes to greet her by the door]

1563
01:22:51,763 --> 01:22:53,403
Were you working, Min Ju?

1564
01:22:53,403 --> 01:22:56,283
- I was...
- Amazing.

1565
01:22:56,283 --> 01:22:58,243
Are you feeling okay?

1566
01:22:58,243 --> 01:23:01,313
I'm okay. How about you?

1567
01:23:01,313 --> 01:23:03,993
I'm totally fine.

1568
01:23:03,993 --> 01:23:07,413
- How?
- I don't know.

1569
01:23:07,413 --> 01:23:10,433
- It's okay.
- Put those on.

1570
01:23:11,403 --> 01:23:12,223
[Grinning]

1571
01:23:14,023 --> 01:23:17,493
- Unni!
- Hey.

1572
01:23:18,373 --> 01:23:20,843
Unni, great work.

1573
01:23:20,843 --> 01:23:23,593
- Did you eat?
- I had Subway.

1574
01:23:23,593 --> 01:23:25,673
- What were you doing? Working?
- Until now?

1575
01:23:25,673 --> 01:23:28,643
I worked and had a meeting.

1576
01:23:28,643 --> 01:23:30,953
- Sit.
- She was doing a lot.

1577
01:23:30,953 --> 01:23:36,923
[Min Ju naturally sits next to Gyu Ri]

1578
01:23:38,303 --> 01:23:40,853
[Staring]

1579
01:23:40,853 --> 01:23:42,663
Want to share this? It's frozen.

1580
01:23:42,663 --> 01:23:46,413
It's okay. I had too many cookies.

1581
01:23:53,183 --> 01:23:55,253
You can have that now.

1582
01:23:55,253 --> 01:23:57,903
Green tangerine-flavored alcohol.

1583
01:23:57,903 --> 01:24:00,033
[Glancing]

1584
01:24:00,033 --> 01:24:02,173
Yu Gyeong is bothered by something.

1585
01:24:02,173 --> 01:24:04,413
I'm curious.

1586
01:24:04,413 --> 01:24:11,843
[A strange mood in the living room]

1587
01:24:12,943 --> 01:24:14,733
- Is it good?
- Yes.

1588
01:24:14,733 --> 01:24:18,323
We should add ice to it, right?

1589
01:24:18,323 --> 01:24:21,433
Are there a lot of employees?

1590
01:24:21,433 --> 01:24:24,323
Maybe thirty people?

1591
01:24:24,323 --> 01:24:27,593
[Gyu Ri and Min Ju only talk to each other]

1592
01:24:34,463 --> 01:24:37,813
[Fidgeting]

1593
01:24:37,813 --> 01:24:42,863
[The same space, different temperatures]

1594
01:24:44,733 --> 01:24:47,263
There's something weird in the air.

1595
01:24:47,263 --> 01:24:49,173
Yu Gyeong is feeling it.

1596
01:24:49,173 --> 01:24:51,443
- I look normal, right?
- What did you do?

1597
01:24:51,443 --> 01:24:53,663
I look good, right?

1598
01:24:56,113 --> 01:24:57,453
Do I look tired?

1599
01:24:57,453 --> 01:24:59,163
[Shaking her head]

1600
01:24:59,163 --> 01:25:03,073
- You just look normal.
- You don't look tired.

1601
01:25:03,073 --> 01:25:06,063
I don't look tired, right?

1602
01:25:06,063 --> 01:25:07,963
[Nods]

1603
01:25:09,833 --> 01:25:11,483
[Turning her head]

1604
01:25:18,843 --> 01:25:19,833
[Glancing]

1605
01:25:21,133 --> 01:25:23,023
You look happy, Unni.

1606
01:25:23,023 --> 01:25:25,923
I just know how to enjoy it.

1607
01:25:25,923 --> 01:25:27,973
I keep having wine and cheese alone.

1608
01:25:27,973 --> 01:25:30,053
Right. You're bringing up the vibes
by yourself.

1609
01:25:30,053 --> 01:25:32,933
- I'm curious, can I try it?
- Sure.

1610
01:25:32,933 --> 01:25:38,973
[Feeling distant for some reason]

1611
01:25:42,293 --> 01:25:45,803
It just tastes like wine,
but it's pretty weak.

1612
01:25:47,153 --> 01:25:53,443
[A strange sense of anxiety approaches]

1613
01:25:53,443 --> 01:25:56,223
Smell the whiskey. It's so good.

1614
01:25:56,223 --> 01:25:57,563
You drink whiskey?

1615
01:25:57,563 --> 01:25:59,043
[Her face begins to grow stiff]

1616
01:25:59,043 --> 01:26:01,103
I would want to leave.

1617
01:26:01,103 --> 01:26:04,193
Everyone is alone in the same space.

1618
01:26:14,103 --> 01:26:17,323
She won't look over there.

1619
01:26:17,323 --> 01:26:18,503
[Spinning her head]

1620
01:26:25,313 --> 01:26:29,923
[Her gaze is in one direction]

1621
01:26:29,923 --> 01:26:33,263
[His eyes are lost]

1622
01:26:35,323 --> 01:26:37,693
[Staring]

1623
01:26:41,023 --> 01:26:43,713
[Glaring]

1624
01:26:45,463 --> 01:26:47,533
[What will these anxious feelings lead to?]

1625
01:26:47,533 --> 01:26:49,513
What do we do?

1626
01:26:49,513 --> 01:26:53,533
[What will these anxious feelings lead to?]

1627
01:26:53,533 --> 01:26:56,573
Have we seen Gyu Ri overcompensate like this?

1628
01:26:56,573 --> 01:26:58,923
- It's unnatural.
- She's overcompensating.

1629
01:26:58,923 --> 01:27:01,383
Intentionally or not, Yu Gyeong is excluded.

1630
01:27:01,383 --> 01:27:07,143
Yu Gyeong is just in an awkward spot.

1631
01:27:07,143 --> 01:27:11,353
She might get uncomfortable,
so the three stick together.

1632
01:27:11,353 --> 01:27:14,273
A lot of conversation took place
while Yu Gyeong was gone.

1633
01:27:14,273 --> 01:27:19,003
But everyone is there,
and it's the three of them talking.

1634
01:27:19,003 --> 01:27:20,913
Yu Gyeong feels it, too.

1635
01:27:20,913 --> 01:27:25,023
She and Gyu Ri already have a history.

1636
01:27:25,023 --> 01:27:28,973
She said that she was smiling
as she walked in,

1637
01:27:28,973 --> 01:27:33,373
saying "I'm home!" but they were
laughing by themselves.

1638
01:27:33,373 --> 01:27:38,013
She was thinking it over
while sitting with everyone,

1639
01:27:38,013 --> 01:27:41,123
and suddenly brought it up with a smile.

1640
01:27:41,123 --> 01:27:45,623
I think she's moving strategically.

1641
01:27:45,623 --> 01:27:47,743
Should we get back here after 10 minutes?

1642
01:27:47,743 --> 01:27:50,133
- Sure.
- Sounds good.

1643
01:27:52,413 --> 01:27:54,613
[The tenants leave]

1644
01:27:56,363 --> 01:27:58,193
It's Min Ju's.

1645
01:27:58,193 --> 01:28:00,313
I have the same battery.

1646
01:28:00,313 --> 01:28:02,023
I'll go out to the veranda.

1647
01:28:02,023 --> 01:28:03,373
[Sliding]

1648
01:28:06,463 --> 01:28:10,023
[Just the two of them remain]

1649
01:28:15,583 --> 01:28:17,173
Her face has changed.

1650
01:28:17,173 --> 01:28:20,913
[Maybe because of the vibes just now]

1651
01:28:23,333 --> 01:28:24,643
[The two are now silent]

1652
01:28:24,643 --> 01:28:27,133
They can't help but think about it.

1653
01:28:29,723 --> 01:28:32,923
My fingers are yellow from the tangerines.

1654
01:28:32,923 --> 01:28:36,273
You ate all the tangerines.

1655
01:28:36,273 --> 01:28:38,143
Have more.

1656
01:28:39,143 --> 01:28:42,333
Are you okay with drinking?

1657
01:28:42,333 --> 01:28:43,743
Am I red?

1658
01:28:43,743 --> 01:28:45,733
A little bit?

1659
01:28:45,733 --> 01:28:49,453
You're a little red over here,
but yellow here.

1660
01:28:49,453 --> 01:28:51,863
What's that?

1661
01:28:51,863 --> 01:28:54,323
It's a variety.

1662
01:28:54,323 --> 01:28:58,343
If we wake up early tomorrow,
will we be tired?

1663
01:28:59,603 --> 01:29:00,963
Want me to take you?

1664
01:29:00,963 --> 01:29:02,933
No.

1665
01:29:02,933 --> 01:29:04,423
Me?

1666
01:29:04,423 --> 01:29:06,213
Want to come to my office?

1667
01:29:07,103 --> 01:29:08,843
Should I?

1668
01:29:10,893 --> 01:29:15,923
Sounds nice.
But you won't want to be in my car.

1669
01:29:15,923 --> 01:29:18,663
I'll drive.

1670
01:29:18,663 --> 01:29:20,203
Why do you not trust me?

1671
01:29:20,203 --> 01:29:22,313
I do trust you.

1672
01:29:22,313 --> 01:29:27,013
I just feel awkward. I've almost
never been in someone else's car.

1673
01:29:27,013 --> 01:29:30,553
Really? Me neither.

1674
01:29:30,553 --> 01:29:33,393
- I always drive.
- Same.

1675
01:29:33,393 --> 01:29:35,963
- You must be good.
- Of course.

1676
01:29:35,963 --> 01:29:39,063
- But I've been in an accident.
- You have?

1677
01:29:40,283 --> 01:29:42,403
It's fun.

1678
01:29:42,403 --> 01:29:43,953
- They're still laughing.
- Cute.

1679
01:29:43,953 --> 01:29:48,813
- You're so smooth.
- Am I?

1680
01:29:48,813 --> 01:29:51,653
I won't drive while I'm here.

1681
01:29:51,653 --> 01:29:52,923
Go ahead.

1682
01:29:52,923 --> 01:29:56,023
I think I'll have a chance. Of course.

1683
01:29:56,023 --> 01:29:59,053
Can I be a back-seat driver?

1684
01:29:59,053 --> 01:30:01,203
"That was a little rough..."

1685
01:30:02,303 --> 01:30:05,843
I'll probably agree with you.

1686
01:30:10,393 --> 01:30:12,573
Aigoo.

1687
01:30:12,573 --> 01:30:14,613
[A little while ago, at dinner]

1688
01:30:16,453 --> 01:30:18,223
It bothers her.

1689
01:30:18,223 --> 01:30:19,643
[Grinning]

1690
01:30:23,793 --> 01:30:25,253
Don't regret it later. Have plenty.

1691
01:30:25,253 --> 01:30:26,963
I won't regret it.

1692
01:30:26,963 --> 01:30:29,083
I don't make regrettable choices.

1693
01:30:30,273 --> 01:30:32,223
She must feel conflicted.

1694
01:30:35,453 --> 01:30:37,783
Noona, you're not eating enough.

1695
01:30:37,783 --> 01:30:40,203
"I can't eat. It's your fault."

1696
01:30:40,203 --> 01:30:42,563
[Feeling uncomfortable]

1697
01:30:47,053 --> 01:30:51,103
[Even a single text feels overwhelming today]

1698
01:30:52,813 --> 01:30:54,573
Did you send?

1699
01:30:55,893 --> 01:30:58,893
- I haven't.
- You haven't?

1700
01:30:58,893 --> 01:31:00,393
[So Yun closes the door]

1701
01:31:01,113 --> 01:31:03,243
You haven't?

1702
01:31:03,243 --> 01:31:05,383
You're still debating?

1703
01:31:10,813 --> 01:31:15,513
Why? Are you debating between...

1704
01:31:15,513 --> 01:31:18,783
going for it and going around it?

1705
01:31:18,783 --> 01:31:21,343
- Or a new person?
- I just don't know how I feel.

1706
01:31:21,343 --> 01:31:23,073
Really?

1707
01:31:23,073 --> 01:31:26,073
Why? Are you not interested anymore?

1708
01:31:26,073 --> 01:31:27,973
I don't know.

1709
01:31:29,833 --> 01:31:32,523
I have no idea what I'm feeling.

1710
01:31:34,023 --> 01:31:35,613
[Flopping down]

1711
01:31:35,613 --> 01:31:37,493
Too complicated.

1712
01:31:41,163 --> 01:31:42,883
What's wrong, So Yun?

1713
01:31:42,883 --> 01:31:46,323
- Jun Hyeon is checking up on her.
- What are you so conflicted about?

1714
01:31:49,303 --> 01:31:51,483
- How was your day today?
- Today?

1715
01:31:51,483 --> 01:31:53,373
Did you have fun? Were you well?

1716
01:31:53,373 --> 01:31:55,673
- No, I was not well.
- How come?

1717
01:31:55,673 --> 01:31:57,343
I thought you did a bunch of fun things?

1718
01:31:57,343 --> 01:31:59,373
No.

1719
01:31:59,373 --> 01:32:01,273
I barely did anything.

1720
01:32:01,273 --> 01:32:03,173
Really?

1721
01:32:04,753 --> 01:32:06,773
Why? You have a lot on your mind?

1722
01:32:06,773 --> 01:32:09,873
No, I mean...

1723
01:32:09,873 --> 01:32:11,223
She can't tell him.

1724
01:32:11,223 --> 01:32:13,633
[Sighs]

1725
01:32:14,613 --> 01:32:17,783
Why is this text so stressful?

1726
01:32:17,783 --> 01:32:20,153
Text? Is it stressful?

1727
01:32:20,153 --> 01:32:23,163
Is it stressful to send? Or...

1728
01:32:24,073 --> 01:32:25,463
Both?

1729
01:32:25,463 --> 01:32:30,023
[Wu Yeol passes them]

1730
01:32:31,783 --> 01:32:34,253
- Sending it?
- Yeah.

1731
01:32:34,253 --> 01:32:35,963
I get it.

1732
01:32:35,963 --> 01:32:37,693
[Looking up]

1733
01:32:40,463 --> 01:32:42,103
My hair...

1734
01:32:42,103 --> 01:32:44,293
That makes sense.

1735
01:32:44,293 --> 01:32:46,063
It does?

1736
01:32:48,443 --> 01:32:51,603
- Should I do it?
- You haven't yet?

1737
01:32:51,603 --> 01:32:53,833
[She finally sends the text]

1738
01:32:58,953 --> 01:33:03,953
[Did you detect their heart signals?]

1739
01:33:03,953 --> 01:33:09,153
[Predict the eight people's
love lines based on clues!]

1740
01:33:09,153 --> 01:33:11,423
I really can't guess this one.

1741
01:33:11,423 --> 01:33:15,263
"This one?" That is not the right word.

1742
01:33:15,263 --> 01:33:17,273
Maybe not in this life.

1743
01:33:17,273 --> 01:33:20,243
Let's do the easy ones first.

1744
01:33:20,243 --> 01:33:22,313
Wu Yeol and Yu Gyeong.

1745
01:33:22,313 --> 01:33:23,733
They're done.

1746
01:33:23,733 --> 01:33:25,743
They're fixed.

1747
01:33:25,743 --> 01:33:27,033
Yu Gyeong will pick Wu Yeol, too.

1748
01:33:27,033 --> 01:33:29,743
This has to go this way.

1749
01:33:29,743 --> 01:33:32,873
Seo Won will pick Gyu Ri.

1750
01:33:32,873 --> 01:33:35,773
Sure, sure. Let's do the easy stuff first.

1751
01:33:35,773 --> 01:33:37,333
So Yun!

1752
01:33:37,333 --> 01:33:40,503
I think So Yun will pick Jun Hyeon.
She's run into him a lot.

1753
01:33:40,503 --> 01:33:43,573
Jun Hyeon read So Yun's mind.

1754
01:33:43,573 --> 01:33:44,693
Right, right.

1755
01:33:44,693 --> 01:33:46,653
[He sat with her when she was struggling]

1756
01:33:46,653 --> 01:33:48,323
No, I wasn't well.

1757
01:33:48,323 --> 01:33:51,023
I don't think So Yun wants this,

1758
01:33:51,023 --> 01:33:54,763
but she knows it's not going to
work out with Wu Yeol.

1759
01:33:54,763 --> 01:33:57,863
- She wants to give up.
- That's why she won't text him.

1760
01:33:57,863 --> 01:33:59,063
I think Jun Hyeon.

1761
01:33:59,063 --> 01:34:03,063
I think Jun Hyeon is the only option.
It's not Wu Yeol.

1762
01:34:03,063 --> 01:34:05,233
A lot of these are hard.

1763
01:34:05,233 --> 01:34:06,833
What about Min Ju?

1764
01:34:06,833 --> 01:34:09,263
I think Min Ju will go with Jun Hyeon.

1765
01:34:09,263 --> 01:34:11,363
Because he drove her.

1766
01:34:11,363 --> 01:34:13,383
I think Seong Min.

1767
01:34:13,383 --> 01:34:17,293
She keeps complaining about him
because she likes him.

1768
01:34:17,293 --> 01:34:19,843
But Seong Min's actions,

1769
01:34:19,843 --> 01:34:22,683
what he said in the tea room made it hard...

1770
01:34:22,683 --> 01:34:26,893
[Min Ju was disturbed by what Seong Min said]

1771
01:34:27,723 --> 01:34:30,603
It's hard from Min Ju's perspective.

1772
01:34:30,603 --> 01:34:33,663
- Min Ju has pride, too.
- She needs to play hard to get.

1773
01:34:33,663 --> 01:34:36,323
I hope she doesn't, strategically.

1774
01:34:36,323 --> 01:34:38,293
Let's go with the strategy.

1775
01:34:38,293 --> 01:34:40,233
I think it's Jun Hyeon.

1776
01:34:40,233 --> 01:34:42,483
She has to stop.

1777
01:34:42,483 --> 01:34:44,743
- We have a lot left.
- Gyu Ri.

1778
01:34:44,743 --> 01:34:46,863
I think Gyu Ri will go with Seo Won.

1779
01:34:46,863 --> 01:34:48,723
I don't know.

1780
01:34:48,723 --> 01:34:51,063
Why, why, why?

1781
01:34:51,063 --> 01:34:56,043
I have a feeling
she's going with Park Wu Yeol.

1782
01:34:56,043 --> 01:35:01,303
It's war. There's still time left to
get to know each other.

1783
01:35:01,303 --> 01:35:02,983
Gyu Ri will go for it.

1784
01:35:02,983 --> 01:35:05,603
- She's going to shake up Wu Yeol?
- Yes.

1785
01:35:05,603 --> 01:35:07,543
But the flowers!

1786
01:35:07,543 --> 01:35:10,873
Seo Won was the only one who made her happy.

1787
01:35:10,873 --> 01:35:12,863
Whenever she comes home,

1788
01:35:12,863 --> 01:35:15,703
he goes, "Noona, why are you so late?"

1789
01:35:15,703 --> 01:35:18,263
He always greets her when she comes home.

1790
01:35:18,263 --> 01:35:19,363
Gyu Ri and Seo Won?

1791
01:35:19,363 --> 01:35:21,413
- Her heart is with Wu Yeol.
- Of course.

1792
01:35:21,413 --> 01:35:24,073
But she'll send the text to Seo Won, I think.

1793
01:35:24,073 --> 01:35:26,843
- Okay.
- I hope I'm right.

1794
01:35:26,843 --> 01:35:28,673
Seong Min.

1795
01:35:28,673 --> 01:35:29,863
Where is Seong Min going?

1796
01:35:29,863 --> 01:35:31,663
It has to be Min Ju.

1797
01:35:31,663 --> 01:35:33,843
- I'm going with Yu Gyeong.
- Me, too.

1798
01:35:33,843 --> 01:35:36,303
- I think it's Min Ju.
- Min Ju?

1799
01:35:36,303 --> 01:35:39,613
I think it's Yu Gyeong because of the memo.

1800
01:35:39,613 --> 01:35:43,083
There was a response. He asked for a date.

1801
01:35:43,083 --> 01:35:45,583
Do you want to go out for dinner on Friday?

1802
01:35:45,583 --> 01:35:48,893
I think he'll text her about the date.

1803
01:35:48,893 --> 01:35:52,463
I agree. Something like
"How does beef sound?"

1804
01:35:52,463 --> 01:35:58,783
If Seong Min knew he was going
to text and ask out Yu Gyeong,

1805
01:35:58,783 --> 01:36:02,223
so he was implying that to
Min Ju in the tea room?

1806
01:36:02,223 --> 01:36:04,463
I'm not watching him.

1807
01:36:04,463 --> 01:36:07,023
I'm not watching Seong Min.

1808
01:36:07,023 --> 01:36:10,823
We're 2 to 2. Tsuki, you pick.

1809
01:36:10,823 --> 01:36:13,693
Me? I pick Yu Gyeong.

1810
01:36:13,693 --> 01:36:16,313
- Yu Gyeong?
- Okay, Yu Gyeong.

1811
01:36:16,313 --> 01:36:18,163
Tsuki made this choice!

1812
01:36:18,163 --> 01:36:20,693
I've been wrong every time!

1813
01:36:20,693 --> 01:36:24,173
Well, it's just a guess.

1814
01:36:24,173 --> 01:36:26,833
Jun Hyeon.

1815
01:36:26,833 --> 01:36:29,053
Jun Hyeon is confusing. Yu Gyeong?

1816
01:36:29,053 --> 01:36:30,673
I think he's into Yu Gyeong still.

1817
01:36:30,673 --> 01:36:34,823
Jun Hyeon might not let it show
until the text.

1818
01:36:34,823 --> 01:36:37,983
Ever since he made up his mind,

1819
01:36:37,983 --> 01:36:40,323
- I don't think he's changed.
- I think he's for Yu Gyeong.

1820
01:36:40,323 --> 01:36:42,483
Yu Gyeong.

1821
01:36:42,483 --> 01:36:45,133
- I don't think I'm right today.
- Of course not.

1822
01:36:45,133 --> 01:36:47,073
Let's go!

1823
01:36:47,073 --> 01:36:51,063
[Which way did our hearts turn tonight?]

1824
01:36:51,803 --> 01:36:53,533
[Buzz]

1825
01:36:54,223 --> 01:36:57,023
[Salt Bread: I like your hair]

1826
01:36:57,023 --> 01:36:59,233
"I like your hair."

1827
01:37:04,043 --> 01:37:05,163
[My Dog, Yellow]

1828
01:37:05,163 --> 01:37:08,793
"Do dishes with me tomorrow again."

1829
01:37:09,773 --> 01:37:14,333
[For some, a chance to confirm
each other's feelings]

1830
01:37:16,073 --> 01:37:19,653
[For some, an infinite wait]

1831
01:37:19,653 --> 01:37:22,903
Maybe I won't get anything today.

1832
01:37:24,753 --> 01:37:25,863
[Buzz]

1833
01:37:28,403 --> 01:37:30,443
[Tired Camel: I want to help you move]

1834
01:37:30,443 --> 01:37:32,263
[Dried Sweet Potato:
I'll come home earlier on Friday]

1835
01:37:32,263 --> 01:37:34,213
It's the camel.

1836
01:37:36,403 --> 01:37:39,323
He's so happy.

1837
01:37:41,273 --> 01:37:43,763
[Beluga of the Forest: I'm curious]

1838
01:37:44,653 --> 01:37:48,263
We were correct!

1839
01:37:51,923 --> 01:37:56,353
[Pure Rabbit: You're so funny. Thanks.]

1840
01:37:56,353 --> 01:37:58,563
We got that right!

1841
01:37:58,563 --> 01:38:00,393
We got So Yun right.

1842
01:38:01,313 --> 01:38:02,633
[Buzz]

1843
01:38:03,683 --> 01:38:04,643
[Sleepy Bear]

1844
01:38:04,643 --> 01:38:06,143
"I want to talk."

1845
01:38:06,143 --> 01:38:10,933
[Sleepy Bear]

1846
01:38:11,593 --> 01:38:13,093
She picked Seong Min again?

1847
01:38:13,093 --> 01:38:16,383
Min Ju only has eyes for one.

1848
01:38:16,383 --> 01:38:18,593
I'm watching you, Seong Min.

1849
01:38:18,593 --> 01:38:20,853
Me, too.

1850
01:38:22,613 --> 01:38:26,243
[Busy Hamster: Every day goes by
so fast, wish I could freeze time]

1851
01:38:26,773 --> 01:38:31,413
[Busy Hamster]

1852
01:38:31,413 --> 01:38:33,573
[Shocked]

1853
01:38:33,573 --> 01:38:35,173
[Shock itself]

1854
01:38:35,173 --> 01:38:36,053
Why?

1855
01:38:36,053 --> 01:38:39,073
Seong Min, why did you say that to her then?

1856
01:38:39,073 --> 01:38:41,593
He sent it because he said that.

1857
01:38:41,593 --> 01:38:45,103
- That's who Seong Min is.
- I don't get it.

1858
01:38:45,103 --> 01:38:50,063
Ironically, it means
he has feelings for Min Ju.

1859
01:38:50,063 --> 01:38:51,933
The results speak for themselves.

1860
01:38:51,933 --> 01:38:54,293
I can't trust Tsuki.
She's wrong about everything.

1861
01:38:54,293 --> 01:38:56,663
[Speechless]

1862
01:38:56,663 --> 01:38:59,893
Sure, sure, it was my fault.

1863
01:38:59,893 --> 01:39:02,383
It wasn't my fault today.

1864
01:39:02,383 --> 01:39:05,213
[All texts sent]

1865
01:39:05,213 --> 01:39:07,503
What did you do? I saw.

1866
01:39:07,503 --> 01:39:10,133
The door is flimsy.

1867
01:39:10,133 --> 01:39:12,063
"Flimsy."

1868
01:39:12,063 --> 01:39:16,763
[A text arrives
after all texts have been sent]

1869
01:39:19,463 --> 01:39:29,463
[Pure Rabbit wants to meet with Salt Bread]

1870
01:39:30,723 --> 01:39:35,683
[A request for a date
unbeknownst to anyone else]

1871
01:39:36,943 --> 01:39:42,223
[Time to confront the feelings
that are still there]

1872
01:39:42,223 --> 01:39:44,673
From all the nicknames
you've received texts from,

1873
01:39:44,673 --> 01:39:48,223
ask out the one you want
to get to know on a date.

1874
01:39:48,223 --> 01:39:50,603
Let's begin the "nickname dates."

1875
01:39:50,603 --> 01:39:53,873
Only one person has to request it.

1876
01:39:53,873 --> 01:39:55,403
It can be one-sided.

1877
01:39:55,403 --> 01:39:57,313
- It's an opportunity.
- Right.

1878
01:39:57,313 --> 01:40:01,473
From Wu Yeol's perspective,
he has to wrap it up.

1879
01:40:01,473 --> 01:40:03,133
Right, he could feel uneasy.

1880
01:40:03,133 --> 01:40:06,793
If I don't end it with her, I'll feel bad.

1881
01:40:06,793 --> 01:40:08,083
He seems accepting.

1882
01:40:08,083 --> 01:40:12,223
Then, all the other guys
can work on Yu Gyeong.

1883
01:40:12,223 --> 01:40:14,413
- Jun Hyeon, Seong Min...
- Right.

1884
01:40:14,413 --> 01:40:18,073
Jun Hyeon texted her today.

1885
01:40:18,073 --> 01:40:19,973
On top of that,

1886
01:40:19,973 --> 01:40:23,413
Yu Gyeong is conscious of her
relationships with the ladies.

1887
01:40:23,413 --> 01:40:26,693
- She's the youngest.
- She might be struggling.

1888
01:40:26,693 --> 01:40:28,263
Everyone is struggling.

1889
01:40:28,263 --> 01:40:32,283
Then a real war is going to begin.

1890
01:40:32,283 --> 01:40:35,003
[After dates in Japan and Korea]

1891
01:40:35,883 --> 01:40:37,953
How was Japan?

1892
01:40:37,953 --> 01:40:41,383
We walked a lot. My legs hurt.

1893
01:40:41,383 --> 01:40:45,283
I think I walked 15,000 steps that day.

1894
01:40:45,283 --> 01:40:47,513
That's probably tiring.

1895
01:40:47,513 --> 01:40:49,063
I need a massage.

1896
01:40:49,063 --> 01:40:50,723
Let's do this.

1897
01:40:53,013 --> 01:40:54,903
Thank you.

1898
01:40:54,903 --> 01:40:57,523
It works so well.

1899
01:40:57,523 --> 01:40:59,523
They're like boots.

1900
01:40:59,523 --> 01:41:03,663
[Detoxing after the dates]

1901
01:41:03,663 --> 01:41:05,203
It's working.

1902
01:41:06,263 --> 01:41:08,533
It feels so good.

1903
01:41:08,533 --> 01:41:12,923
If you press it one more time, it changes.

1904
01:41:12,923 --> 01:41:16,173
I want it to be a little warmer.

1905
01:41:16,173 --> 01:41:19,933
- So warm. I have such cold hands and feet.
- Me, too.

1906
01:41:19,933 --> 01:41:23,023
It feels so good.

1907
01:41:23,023 --> 01:41:25,943
Just your calves can send you to heaven.

1908
01:41:27,633 --> 01:41:30,413
It feels so good.

1909
01:41:30,413 --> 01:41:35,443
- My skin has been so dry since Japan.
- Same.

1910
01:41:35,443 --> 01:41:37,513
I don't look great.

1911
01:41:37,513 --> 01:41:40,093
I need to go get a facial sometime.

1912
01:41:40,093 --> 01:41:41,483
- Want to go with me?
- Sounds good.

1913
01:41:41,483 --> 01:41:44,123
Let's go. Let's change first.

1914
01:41:46,123 --> 01:41:48,463
I'm so excited.

1915
01:41:49,453 --> 01:41:54,093
[These two are here for some healing]

1916
01:41:54,093 --> 01:41:56,883
Yay, facials.

1917
01:41:56,883 --> 01:41:59,153
What are your skincare concerns?

1918
01:41:59,153 --> 01:42:01,643
I'm a little dry.

1919
01:42:01,643 --> 01:42:05,583
When I put on makeup, these parts are patchy.

1920
01:42:05,583 --> 01:42:11,193
After today,
you can resume everyday activities.

1921
01:42:11,193 --> 01:42:12,723
We'll take good care of you.

1922
01:42:12,723 --> 01:42:14,633
Thank you!

1923
01:42:14,633 --> 01:42:16,353
Here we go.

1924
01:42:20,763 --> 01:42:23,033
[Moist]

1925
01:42:23,033 --> 01:42:28,373
I'll look good for my date after this.

1926
01:42:28,373 --> 01:42:32,143
Do this the night before a date.

1927
01:42:32,143 --> 01:42:34,403
What a treat.

1928
01:42:34,403 --> 01:42:35,833
[So happy]

1929
01:42:37,213 --> 01:42:39,573
My skin feels tighter.

1930
01:42:39,573 --> 01:42:41,343
My makeup sits better.

1931
01:42:41,343 --> 01:42:44,183
You look really good.

1932
01:42:44,183 --> 01:42:47,023
- I think I'm glowing.
- You look so much better.

1933
01:42:47,023 --> 01:42:51,563
[A day complete after a moment of rest]

1934
01:42:51,563 --> 01:42:54,503
[How well do we know each other?]

1935
01:42:55,943 --> 01:43:01,393
[Which nickname are you most
curious to know who?]

1936
01:43:03,213 --> 01:43:07,573
[Time to look at the feelings
behind the nicknames]

1937
01:43:07,573 --> 01:43:10,373
[Debating]

1938
01:43:12,613 --> 01:43:17,583
[Some people follow their certainty]

1939
01:43:17,583 --> 01:43:22,283
[Some people follow their curiosity]

1940
01:43:22,283 --> 01:43:26,833
[With these choices]

1941
01:43:28,033 --> 01:43:32,863
[What kind of hidden feelings
will be revealed?]

1942
01:43:36,693 --> 01:43:40,413
[A noisy evening commute]

1943
01:43:40,993 --> 01:43:43,233
["Pure Rabbit" So Yun awaits...]

1944
01:43:45,363 --> 01:43:46,833
[Nervous]

1945
01:43:51,773 --> 01:43:52,883
["Salt Bread" Wu Yeol]

1946
01:43:52,883 --> 01:43:54,453
Pure Rabbit to Salt Bread.

1947
01:43:54,453 --> 01:43:56,703
So Yun requested Wu Yeol.

1948
01:43:56,703 --> 01:43:58,653
Hey.

1949
01:43:58,653 --> 01:44:00,313
Hello.

1950
01:44:05,243 --> 01:44:07,333
[These two face each other after a while]

1951
01:44:08,553 --> 01:44:10,173
[Distant]

1952
01:44:12,843 --> 01:44:14,553
[Glancing]

1953
01:44:18,493 --> 01:44:21,333
It's a little warmer now.

1954
01:44:21,333 --> 01:44:25,633
Yesterday and today were good, weather-wise.

1955
01:44:25,633 --> 01:44:27,033
Agreed.

1956
01:44:28,273 --> 01:44:29,443
Hahaha...

1957
01:44:29,443 --> 01:44:33,343
So dry. It's not like the usual.

1958
01:44:33,343 --> 01:44:36,893
Soju? Should we have soju?

1959
01:44:36,893 --> 01:44:38,593
He wants to drink.

1960
01:44:38,593 --> 01:44:41,653
Are you determined today?

1961
01:44:45,883 --> 01:44:48,663
[Fidgeting]

1962
01:44:50,473 --> 01:44:52,773
It's awkward.

1963
01:44:52,773 --> 01:44:55,313
It's so awkward.

1964
01:44:56,273 --> 01:44:58,663
[Biting his lip]

1965
01:45:01,363 --> 01:45:04,293
She needed so much courage for this.

1966
01:45:05,283 --> 01:45:09,753
[After their warm date in Japan]

1967
01:45:10,643 --> 01:45:12,123
What are you doing?

1968
01:45:12,123 --> 01:45:16,103
[Wu Yeol's vibes were somehow different]

1969
01:45:17,933 --> 01:45:22,293
[All they can do is exchange awkward gazes]

1970
01:45:25,753 --> 01:45:27,373
Thank you.

1971
01:45:28,193 --> 01:45:29,803
Let me open it.

1972
01:45:30,953 --> 01:45:32,253
[Glancing]

1973
01:45:45,313 --> 01:45:46,863
It's sweet.

1974
01:45:48,673 --> 01:45:50,883
Maybe I've been down.

1975
01:45:50,883 --> 01:45:52,633
Sometimes soju tastes sweet.

1976
01:45:52,633 --> 01:45:57,503
[Steamed clams and noodles]

1977
01:45:58,533 --> 01:46:01,473
- Eat.
- "Eat."

1978
01:46:04,773 --> 01:46:07,173
- Eat.
- Me?

1979
01:46:07,173 --> 01:46:11,613
You sound like you're talking to a dog.

1980
01:46:12,513 --> 01:46:14,673
Please eat.

1981
01:46:14,673 --> 01:46:17,043
- So Yun is determined.
- They both are.

1982
01:46:17,043 --> 01:46:21,733
You don't... can you eat stuff like this?

1983
01:46:23,143 --> 01:46:25,903
I wasn't expecting this, actually.

1984
01:46:25,903 --> 01:46:29,933
- I wanted broth.
- Right.

1985
01:46:30,933 --> 01:46:33,903
Good, you can have it all.

1986
01:46:35,073 --> 01:46:37,363
- She's funny.
- Have a lot of noodles.

1987
01:46:37,363 --> 01:46:38,953
Thanks.

1988
01:46:40,193 --> 01:46:43,793
[Glasses are going faster than usual]

1989
01:46:45,793 --> 01:46:47,533
It must be hard to talk without alcohol.

1990
01:46:47,533 --> 01:46:49,333
[Hesitating]

1991
01:46:50,153 --> 01:46:53,803
You do get red after drinking beer.

1992
01:46:53,803 --> 01:46:56,053
My cheeks get red.

1993
01:46:56,053 --> 01:47:02,393
I know. You looked like
a hot steamed dumpling.

1994
01:47:04,223 --> 01:47:05,943
The house is a little hot.

1995
01:47:05,943 --> 01:47:07,683
- Am I the only one who feels that?
- Yes.

1996
01:47:07,683 --> 01:47:10,033
[Surprised]

1997
01:47:10,033 --> 01:47:12,603
You just said "Yes."

1998
01:47:12,603 --> 01:47:14,473
Just cutting me off.

1999
01:47:15,343 --> 01:47:17,943
- I'm joking.
- It is hot in the house.

2000
01:47:22,743 --> 01:47:25,983
[Hesitating]

2001
01:47:29,593 --> 01:47:32,493
Did you get a text last night?

2002
01:47:32,493 --> 01:47:34,083
Yes.

2003
01:47:34,083 --> 01:47:36,203
You knew?

2004
01:47:36,203 --> 01:47:38,793
I had a feeling.

2005
01:47:43,773 --> 01:47:46,073
[Hesitating]

2006
01:47:52,493 --> 01:47:57,783
I had more on my mind than I thought I would.

2007
01:47:58,823 --> 01:48:00,733
I beat myself up a lot.

2008
01:48:01,713 --> 01:48:05,413
I did a lot of self-reflection.

2009
01:48:06,433 --> 01:48:07,993
Did you know?

2010
01:48:07,993 --> 01:48:10,253
A little bit?

2011
01:48:12,893 --> 01:48:16,843
This is the second time
I'm eating with you, right?

2012
01:48:16,843 --> 01:48:19,863
No, this is the third time.

2013
01:48:19,863 --> 01:48:22,513
Our first meal,

2014
01:48:22,513 --> 01:48:26,253
then, when we spent the day in Japan,

2015
01:48:26,253 --> 01:48:27,693
then now.

2016
01:48:27,693 --> 01:48:30,253
This is the three times he referred to.

2017
01:48:30,253 --> 01:48:34,963
The date in Japan was big for me, honestly.

2018
01:48:35,843 --> 01:48:40,083
- Right.
- And I thought...

2019
01:48:42,773 --> 01:48:46,003
you had some feelings for me, too.

2020
01:48:46,003 --> 01:48:47,943
She's telling him now.

2021
01:48:50,333 --> 01:48:52,773
We spent the entire day together.

2022
01:48:53,693 --> 01:48:56,323
I think that was my true self.

2023
01:48:58,133 --> 01:49:00,313
It was fun, and I had a good time, but...

2024
01:49:00,313 --> 01:49:04,893
we all got together in the evening, right?

2025
01:49:04,893 --> 01:49:07,963
That's when I felt it.

2026
01:49:07,963 --> 01:49:14,103
That I was noticing
someone in that big group.

2027
01:49:14,103 --> 01:49:15,913
- He's telling her.
- It's for the best.

2028
01:49:15,913 --> 01:49:18,543
Good job.

2029
01:49:18,543 --> 01:49:21,913
You know when you can't help
but look that way.

2030
01:49:21,913 --> 01:49:24,723
- That's when he knew, too.
- He made up his mind.

2031
01:49:24,723 --> 01:49:29,513
In that process, when we came back to Korea,

2032
01:49:30,953 --> 01:49:34,983
I think I was trying
to tie up some loose ends.

2033
01:49:34,983 --> 01:49:38,053
- He's doing well.
- This is for the best.

2034
01:49:39,143 --> 01:49:42,603
Of course, I don't like having
to say this to you directly.

2035
01:49:42,603 --> 01:49:44,143
Who would?

2036
01:49:44,143 --> 01:49:46,713
I don't know how you feel, either.

2037
01:49:47,673 --> 01:49:50,253
I'm sure it's not great.

2038
01:49:54,063 --> 01:49:59,113
It feels more confusing to talk around it.

2039
01:49:59,113 --> 01:50:01,113
I'll just say it.

2040
01:50:04,833 --> 01:50:09,793
I've been wondering
why you were acting like that.

2041
01:50:11,163 --> 01:50:14,623
Until the Japan date,

2042
01:50:14,623 --> 01:50:21,083
I had no idea who was interested in whom.

2043
01:50:21,083 --> 01:50:23,083
Right, it hadn't been that long.

2044
01:50:23,083 --> 01:50:25,453
I know. It was such a short lead-up.

2045
01:50:25,453 --> 01:50:29,553
I had no idea you had feelings for Yu Gyeong.

2046
01:50:33,113 --> 01:50:37,943
I asked Min Ju and Gyu Ri.

2047
01:50:37,943 --> 01:50:41,393
Was there something between
Yu Gyeong and Wu Yeol when I wasn't here?

2048
01:50:41,393 --> 01:50:46,833
The movie date
was already a thing before Japan.

2049
01:50:46,833 --> 01:50:50,593
Wu Yeol had feelings for Yu Gyeong?

2050
01:50:50,593 --> 01:50:52,983
I don't know about that.

2051
01:50:52,983 --> 01:50:57,233
But there was a week before
you got here that you can't ignore.

2052
01:50:57,233 --> 01:51:01,233
- We're seeing the impact of that.
- A week is huge.

2053
01:51:01,233 --> 01:51:05,033
Even if I knew, not much would be different.

2054
01:51:05,033 --> 01:51:07,253
But...

2055
01:51:09,193 --> 01:51:12,423
- you were avoiding me.
- She's being straightforward.

2056
01:51:12,423 --> 01:51:14,573
- Right.
- Right?

2057
01:51:14,573 --> 01:51:16,903
He's admitting it.

2058
01:51:16,903 --> 01:51:18,723
I think so.

2059
01:51:19,643 --> 01:51:22,783
Maybe because I knew
you were interested in me,

2060
01:51:22,783 --> 01:51:24,513
at some point,

2061
01:51:25,663 --> 01:51:27,813
I was avoiding eye contact.

2062
01:51:27,813 --> 01:51:29,893
Well...

2063
01:51:29,893 --> 01:51:36,143
I haven't had to deal with it
in a big group yet.

2064
01:51:36,143 --> 01:51:39,143
- Right.
- Right. What can you do?

2065
01:51:39,143 --> 01:51:43,263
I found myself avoiding
eye contact without trying to.

2066
01:51:44,333 --> 01:51:48,683
[They knew they were just
out of each other's sights]

2067
01:51:50,243 --> 01:51:52,453
[But Wu Yeol avoided her,
getting further away]

2068
01:51:54,273 --> 01:51:57,223
I'm sure you felt that.

2069
01:51:58,223 --> 01:52:02,113
I don't think I dealt with it very well.

2070
01:52:03,053 --> 01:52:05,413
I wanted to be comfortable...

2071
01:52:05,413 --> 01:52:09,023
So, I was avoidant without trying to be.

2072
01:52:09,023 --> 01:52:11,443
- Are you atoning?
- I mean it.

2073
01:52:11,443 --> 01:52:14,263
It's best to be honest about these things.

2074
01:52:14,263 --> 01:52:20,253
I thought it might be tough for you, too.

2075
01:52:21,273 --> 01:52:23,383
It was weighing on my mind.

2076
01:52:23,383 --> 01:52:29,763
Of course, I was hurt and struggling.

2077
01:52:29,763 --> 01:52:36,463
But you avoiding me is giving
someone else certainty.

2078
01:52:36,463 --> 01:52:38,703
Right.

2079
01:52:39,703 --> 01:52:44,233
- I thought you were cool for doing that.
- Same.

2080
01:52:44,233 --> 01:52:47,583
Of course not cool to me.

2081
01:52:47,583 --> 01:52:49,573
But I thought you were a decent guy for that.

2082
01:52:49,573 --> 01:52:53,903
So I hope you don't feel bad for me anymore.

2083
01:52:53,903 --> 01:52:57,113
- So cool!
- I like So Yun.

2084
01:52:57,113 --> 01:53:01,123
Also, I wanted to say thank you.

2085
01:53:01,123 --> 01:53:03,903
Regardless of how things went,

2086
01:53:03,903 --> 01:53:07,703
you were the first person
I felt comfortable with here.

2087
01:53:07,703 --> 01:53:11,743
I could get used to things, thanks to you.

2088
01:53:13,533 --> 01:53:17,333
We made good memories.

2089
01:53:20,613 --> 01:53:22,483
Thank you for telling me.

2090
01:53:23,553 --> 01:53:28,683
No, I wanted to clear the air, too.

2091
01:53:28,683 --> 01:53:32,653
I had some regrets, too.

2092
01:53:32,653 --> 01:53:34,613
Like...

2093
01:53:36,723 --> 01:53:39,513
There were some things I said, like...

2094
01:53:39,513 --> 01:53:41,893
"I only have eyes for one."

2095
01:53:41,893 --> 01:53:44,083
But I go for someone I just fall for.

2096
01:53:44,083 --> 01:53:49,403
When I see him,
I decide in the first 3 seconds.

2097
01:53:49,403 --> 01:53:52,663
I kept trying to apply that to you.

2098
01:53:52,663 --> 01:53:55,603
But when we started talking in a group...

2099
01:53:55,603 --> 01:53:58,053
I realized...

2100
01:53:58,053 --> 01:54:00,383
getting to know each other
through these talks,

2101
01:54:00,383 --> 01:54:07,023
I learned I was capable of being
interested in others, too.

2102
01:54:07,933 --> 01:54:11,753
If I had gotten to know everyone
from the start,

2103
01:54:11,753 --> 01:54:15,913
you would not have felt all this so much.

2104
01:54:15,913 --> 01:54:18,623
I wouldn't have limited myself, either.

2105
01:54:18,623 --> 01:54:19,873
I know what she means.

2106
01:54:19,873 --> 01:54:24,223
I think I was too...

2107
01:54:24,223 --> 01:54:28,983
overconfident in myself. I regretted that.

2108
01:54:28,983 --> 01:54:30,863
- Sure.
- Exactly.

2109
01:54:30,863 --> 01:54:37,083
I thought my honesty
might be a burden to you.

2110
01:54:38,623 --> 01:54:44,463
Even if I just go for who I like,

2111
01:54:44,463 --> 01:54:47,513
I don't want to do that
if it's a burden to him.

2112
01:54:47,513 --> 01:54:50,103
So Yun is amazing for being able to say this.

2113
01:54:50,103 --> 01:54:53,343
That's not from care.

2114
01:54:54,243 --> 01:54:56,803
That's selfishness.

2115
01:54:57,893 --> 01:54:59,223
So cool.

2116
01:54:59,223 --> 01:55:02,213
Now I want you to...

2117
01:55:02,213 --> 01:55:07,603
let go of any negative feelings
you had about me.

2118
01:55:07,603 --> 01:55:11,153
I already have.

2119
01:55:11,153 --> 01:55:16,353
I hope we can both just take what's positive.

2120
01:55:18,383 --> 01:55:21,263
Let's have some soju and shake it off.

2121
01:55:21,263 --> 01:55:22,823
[Cheers]

2122
01:55:22,823 --> 01:55:25,783
[They finally smile]

2123
01:55:25,783 --> 01:55:27,913
- So cool!
- Seriously.

2124
01:55:27,913 --> 01:55:31,443
I feel like you could
write lyrics about them.

2125
01:55:31,443 --> 01:55:34,753
Wu Yeol started well,
but she responded so well.

2126
01:55:34,753 --> 01:55:37,043
This is a sad but happy ending.

2127
01:55:37,043 --> 01:55:39,023
They're both so cool.

2128
01:55:40,223 --> 01:55:43,273
This is nice.

2129
01:55:44,553 --> 01:55:46,873
[Feeling lighter]

2130
01:55:48,023 --> 01:55:51,183
I kept thinking about this while at work.

2131
01:55:51,183 --> 01:55:52,623
Really?

2132
01:55:52,623 --> 01:55:56,013
I didn't know how to bring it up.

2133
01:55:56,013 --> 01:55:58,853
You should have just come to me.

2134
01:55:58,853 --> 01:56:00,413
"Noona!"

2135
01:56:00,413 --> 01:56:03,183
How can I just come up to you?

2136
01:56:03,183 --> 01:56:05,413
Honestly...

2137
01:56:06,343 --> 01:56:08,103
That ring?

2138
01:56:08,103 --> 01:56:09,543
[Chuckling]

2139
01:56:09,543 --> 01:56:12,453
I really wanted to wear it.

2140
01:56:12,453 --> 01:56:15,213
But I couldn't.

2141
01:56:15,213 --> 01:56:19,243
I really want to wear it, too.

2142
01:56:19,243 --> 01:56:20,543
[Laughing]

2143
01:56:20,543 --> 01:56:23,983
But here, it's an important prop.

2144
01:56:23,983 --> 01:56:25,283
So I don't.

2145
01:56:25,283 --> 01:56:27,313
[The controversial rings
are forever hidden away]

2146
01:56:28,173 --> 01:56:30,893
Thanks for telling me.

2147
01:56:30,893 --> 01:56:32,693
Thanks for waiting.

2148
01:56:34,293 --> 01:56:37,673
[Time flows again between the two]

2149
01:56:37,673 --> 01:56:40,973
[What changes will happen to them next?]

2150
01:56:40,973 --> 01:56:42,233
Yay!

2151
01:56:42,233 --> 01:56:44,013
- They did so well.
- Beautiful.

2152
01:56:44,013 --> 01:56:47,423
This is a great example of a good breakup.

2153
01:56:47,423 --> 01:56:50,363
This is... daebak.

2154
01:56:50,363 --> 01:56:51,323
[So moved over here]

2155
01:56:51,323 --> 01:56:53,623
This is a happy ending
that's not a happy ending.

2156
01:56:53,623 --> 01:56:55,993
Bittersweet.

2157
01:56:55,993 --> 01:56:57,843
I was never like that in my 20s.

2158
01:56:57,843 --> 01:56:59,953
- Me neither.
- Same.

2159
01:56:59,953 --> 01:57:03,853
- You were infinitely avoidant, right?
- Yes.

2160
01:57:03,853 --> 01:57:06,653
I'm sure So Yun feels great.

2161
01:57:06,653 --> 01:57:07,633
Right.

2162
01:57:07,633 --> 01:57:13,243
She might have been okay if she hadn't
had to see him at the house.

2163
01:57:13,243 --> 01:57:17,413
If they could each just go home,
it would be easier.

2164
01:57:17,413 --> 01:57:21,263
But thankfully, Jun Hyeon was there.

2165
01:57:21,263 --> 01:57:23,383
I'm sorry, but...

2166
01:57:23,383 --> 01:57:26,823
If there's someone I'm interested in...

2167
01:57:27,753 --> 01:57:29,573
Am I not allowed to touch them?

2168
01:57:30,443 --> 01:57:33,203
Were you thinking I would bring this up?

2169
01:57:33,203 --> 01:57:34,963
At that time, yes.

2170
01:57:36,383 --> 01:57:42,313
You wanted to talk to me.
I have a lot to say, too.

2171
01:57:44,503 --> 01:57:47,253
There's a little bit of nervousness.

2172
01:57:47,253 --> 01:57:50,193
Really...

2173
01:57:50,193 --> 01:57:51,673
So pretty.

2174
01:57:51,673 --> 01:57:54,143
I'm going to follow my heart from now on.

2175
01:57:54,143 --> 01:57:55,813
Why?

2176
01:57:55,813 --> 01:57:59,293
I have a question for you, Unni.

2177
01:57:59,293 --> 01:58:01,093
Are you not interested at all?

2178
01:58:01,093 --> 01:58:04,593
You might feel that, but...

2179
01:58:04,593 --> 01:58:07,003
That's not all.

2180
01:58:07,003 --> 01:58:09,483
- I have a gift.
- A gift?

2181
01:58:09,483 --> 01:58:11,983
For Valentine's Day.

2182
01:58:11,983 --> 01:58:14,273
It's Valentine's Day.

2183
01:58:14,273 --> 01:58:17,488
I'm not doing dishes with you anymore.

2184
01:58:17,488 --> 01:58:19,168
Why not?

2185
01:58:20,973 --> 01:58:23,503
Who can be completely certain?
